title: date salad
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: cinnamon streusel coffeecake
directions: Combine nuts, brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour and cinnamon; cut in 1/4 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on sugar; put cherry halves in center of each slice.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Turn batter over fruit and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 43 to 48 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set topping.
Loosen cake from pan; turn upside down on platter.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons per cup of hot water (stronger for iced tea).

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper, salt and paprika.
Brown rice and onions in butter and spread in buttered baking dish.
Add chicken broth and celery salt.
Place chicken on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 2-quart oval baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Crumble sausage into large skillet. Brown over medium-high heat until no longer pink, stirring to separate meat. Drain sausage on paper towels. Discard fat and wipe skillet with paper towel. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in same skillet over medium heat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir until thickened. Add sausage, potatoes and eggs. Stir to combine. Pour into prepared dish. Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter. Combine corn flakes crumbs and melted butter in small bowl. Sprinkle evenly over casserole. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with green onions. Makes 6 servings.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat oil in a 4 to 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat. When oil is sizzling, add onion, garlic and celery.
Stir until onion and celery are just tender.
Crumble in ground turkey and cool, stirring and breaking up the meat, until lightly browned. Stir in red and green bell peppers and continue cooking 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt, paprika, chili powder, oregano and cayenne.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Cook, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with shredded Cheddar.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute the celery, onion and pepper in the butter.
Grease a square pan.
Layer the cooked spaghetti, shrimp (cut lengthwise), cheese and sauce.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Let cool 5 minutes, then cut and serve.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Combine ammonia and milk.
Let stand until ammonia has dissolved.
Cream sugar and lard.
Add salt and eggs and mix well. Add ammonia, milk and lemon oil.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead the dough.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness; cut with square cutter. Prick with fork.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: easy cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers into half moons.
Cut peppers into mouthsize pieces.
Slice Roma tomatoes thinly.
Dice as much onion as desired.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl with Italian dressing. (Best dressing to use is Good Seasons fresh dressing.)
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and flour.
Add the slightly beaten eggs, milk and cream.
Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Reset oven at 350° and finish baking 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hot dogs.
Dip each hot dog into batter and fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain on paper and serve hot.
A popsicle stick can be inserted into end of corn dog.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: You will need a large brown grocery bag.

title: * yummy squares *
directions: Drain fruit cocktail thoroughly.
Combine orange juice concentrate, marshmallows and salt.
Stir over low heat until marshmallows are melted; cool.
Whip cream until stiff and fold into marshmallow mixture.
Fold in 2 cups of fruit, reserving remainder for garnish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Spoon the cream mixture over it.
Chill overnight.
Cut in squares and top with remaining fruit.

title: pastitsio(greek macaroni casserole)
directions: Saute meat in 1/4 pound of butter until brown.
Add tomato paste and season with salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Simmer until liquid has absorbed.
Pour milk, eggs and flour in top of double boiler and cook for 1 minute.
Do not let thicken.
Set aside. Cook macaroni; drain well and add 1/4 pound melted butter or margarine with 1/2 pound Parmesan cheese.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and layer 8 sheets of Phyllo pastry in pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Pour a layer of macaroni over top. Stir 4 tablespoons white sauce into meat mixture and pour over macaroni.
Add remaining macaroni over meat and top with remaining white sauce.
Seal all with 8 more sheets of Phyllo pastry, brushing each sheet generously with melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together. Put in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Better if made the night before baking. Can make and freeze, then bake later.

title: ritz peanut butter crackers(healthy kids snack)
directions: Spread peanut butter on Ritz crackers and top with another cracker.
Melt 1 package white stars in double boiler over low heat.
Spread on top of crackers as frosting and place a chocolate star on top.
You may substitute 1 box of powdered sugar mixed with enough milk to make a thick but spreadable frosting in place of the white stars.
We sometimes top them with M&M's or corn candy.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut top off corn; scrape milky white substance from cob.
This makes about 4 cups kernels.
Mix corn, salt and water together. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add corn; cook over medium heat, stirring to be sure it won't burn on the bottom.
Cook for 15 minutes or until corn is tender.

title: layered delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in 2-quart casserole, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything, except nuts, and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon square dessert
directions: Crust:
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine; add flour and nuts and mix.
Press in bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes; cool.

title: dusty popcorn
directions: In a small saucepan, combine margarine or butter and cinnamon. Heat and stir until margarine is melted.
Drizzle over popcorn. Toss.
Sprinkle cocoa powder over popcorn; toss to mix.
Serves 4.

title: nutritious cat food
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: overnight salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Layer chopped broccoli, celery and bell pepper.
Spread with frozen peas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Slice red onions and spread out over the top of peas. Mix salad dressing and sugar.
Spread over the top of onions. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: chicken scallopini and spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken breasts into half.
Place each half between two pieces of waxed paper.
Pound until 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle chicken evenly with garlic powder and pepper.
Coat with flour. Heat oil and 2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken until done and lightly brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Heat remaining butter in same skillet until melted.
Stir in lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Garnish with chopped parsley and lemon slices.
Serve with spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt together; stir into egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour filling into a bowl. Cover with wax paper and chill.
Turn mixture into mixing bowl; whip with electric mixer.
Add peanut butter and vanilla, creaming together thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell; chill until set.
Top with whipped cream and chopped peanuts.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In frypan, brown sausage (remove from casings); add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Pour off drippings. In large Dutch oven, add water, bouillon, tomatoes, carrots, spices, meat and tomato sauce.
Cook 30 minutes, then add zucchini and tortellini; simmer 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of each serving.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Take rolls out of pan. Slice lengthwise in half with serrated knife.
Place lower half back in pan.
Place a layer of cheese and ham over rolls in pan.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut and peel potatoes to boil.
Put all ingredients in huge pot.
Cook for about half an hour after it boils.

title: angel food cake pudding
directions: In large bowl, break angel food cake into small pieces.
In another bowl, mix vanilla pudding with cup of milk, then add into this, ice cream, then pour over cake.
In bowl, mix strawberry Jell-O and boiling water (1 cup); don't add cold water.
Then add frozen strawberries; mix with Jell-O until thickened, then pour over cake.
Cool, then add Cool Whip.
Very good.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix 2 eggs, slightly beaten with 1 1/2 C of pumpkin. Combine 1/4 C brown sugar, 1/2 C granulated sugar, spices & sugar. Add to pumpkin, stir in evaporated milk. Pour into chilled unbaked pastry shell. Bake in hot oven 425 degrees for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350 degrees and bake 25-35 minutes more or until knife inserted
in custard 2 inches from edge comes out clean.

title: bar-b-que cups
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Add bar-b-que sauce, brown sugar and onion; mix well.
Place each biscuit in a greased muffin pan; press down and up the sides.
Spoon meat mixture into cups; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add mushrooms, green pepper and pimentos.
Cook and stir about 5 minutes.
In a jar, combine water, flour, bouillon and pepper.
Cover jar and shake well to combine ingredients.
Pour combined ingredients into skillet with mushroom mixture.
Cook until thickens.
Add chicken and reheat gently.
Serve with toast or biscuits.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Add sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix well.

title: chicken caesar tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and combine with chicken, broth, dressing and mushrooms in a large mixing bowl.
Place mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together cheese and bread crumbs; sprinkle over spaghetti mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll each individual biscuit into melted butter.
Roll next in cinnamon and sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candy cake
directions: Soak candies in milk overnight or until dissolved. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add milk mixture alternately with dry ingredients, cake flour, baking powder and salt. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into two 9-inch pans that have been lightly greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back to the touch.

title: "banana bread"
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, shortening and eggs with fork.
Add flour and baking soda and milk mixture mixed together.
Mix. Add bananas, salt and pecans.
Grease 2 loaf pans with shortening. Divide equally in pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes and loosen with knife.
Turn over then flip on bottom side (right side up) to cool on wire rack.
Yummy!!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 22 minutes.
When cake is cooked, top with Cool Whip or chocolate syrup.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pat into a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken with orange
directions: Brown chicken under broiler.
Place in dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Place onion slices on top.
Combine orange juice, brown sugar, parsley, soy sauce, ginger, water and sherry; pour over chicken and onions.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Approximately 195 calories per serving.

title: russell's chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Simmer for about an hour.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar melts.
Add a dash of pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup Wesson oil.
Heat 1 minute.
Remove and cool.
Pour dressing over vegetables in large bowl.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat until smooth (this might also be mixed in a blender).
Pour part of batter in a clean funnel with about 5/8-inch opening, holding finger over bottom of funnel.
Drop batter into hot, deep fat (375°).
Swirl in circles from center out.
Make each circle 5 to 6 inches in diameter at widest part.
Turn with long tongs.
Brown on both sides; drain on paper towel.
Serve with sprinkling of powdered sugar, jelly, syrup, molasses or honey.

title: enchiladas (2)
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic, salt, pepper, and onion.
Mix enchilada sauce and cream of chicken soup until heated through. Heat tortilla in a saucepan with butter until just warm.

title: peasant salad(fattouche)
directions: Toast and break bread into small pieces.
Chop all the vegetables; add them to the bread and mix well.
Add mashed garlic, lemon juice and oil; toss well.
Serve on platter. Garnish with pomegranate seeds and a little chopped onion and tomatoes.

title: crawfish fettucini casserole(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Saute first seven ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Add crawfish.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Add half and half and 1/2 of Velveeta and all jalapenos.
Add salt and pepper and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Add cooked noodles.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan and remaining Velveeta. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Take 2 heads of collards, cut the leaves off and throw away the stalk and stems.
Put your collards in the washing machine on gentle cycle (make sure to rinse the machine first) and wash 2 times (or you can wash by hands, one leaf at a time).
Take out any leaves that looks spotted or yellow and brown.
In a big pot, fry some fatback, then add collards.
Add water.
Boil and cook until your collards are tender.
Add some sugar (2 tablespoons), salt and pepper to taste.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first ingredients in order given in large salad bowl. Cover with salad dressing, sugar and vinegar mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine; pack down in a baking dish and bake in a 400° oven until brown.
Set aside and cool. Mix cream
cheese
and	powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix Dream Whip
according
to package directions.
Add cheese and sugar mixture.
Fold
in	pecans.
Spread
on cracker crumbs. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries (if frozen berries
are used, you don't have to set jello).
Pour over cheese mixture and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy okra gumbo
directions: Fry chicken without flour.
Fry okra without meal.
Put all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 40 minutes or longer. Serve over rice.

title: authentic french chocolate cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Stir chocolate and a little milk in saucepan over low heat until chocolate melts. Add butter; stir to melt.
Add sugar and flour; stir quickly so it doesn't get lumpy.
Remove from heat.
Add yolks quickly.
Fold the chocolate mixture into the whites.
Grease an 8-inch pan. Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 35 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Put foil on top if the top browns too quickly.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a large bowl, put broken chips and lettuce; then stir good. Add cheese, tomatoes and green onion; stir well.
Add Ranch Style beans and whole corn.
Add Catalina Dressing and stir well so everything is mixed up well.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and nuts. Mix cream of tartar with egg whites and beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, vanilla and baking powder. Fold in cracker mixture and mix well. Spread evenly in lightly-buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: date balls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and simmer for 8 minutes. Remove from heat and add next 3 ingredients.
When cool enough to handle, form into balls and roll in one cup of fine coconut.

title: cranberry wreath punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice into a large punch bowl.
Stir. Add ginger ale and ice.
Serve at once. (May substitute a fifth of vodka, rum or gin instead of 1 quart of the ginger ale.)
Serves 30.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In casserole dish, combine macaroni, broccoli, Spam and red pepper. In small saucepan stir together milk, cornstarch and pepper until dissolved.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Stir this sauce into Spam mixture in casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and gradually stir in milk.
Cook until bubbly and boil 2 minutes.
Remove and mix 1 cup of mix with the beaten eggs.
Return to batter and cook 2 more minutes. Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked crust and serve with or without topping.

title: mongol soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until hot.
Very simple.
Great in winter!

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat together egg, water and vinegar.
Pour all at once into flour mixture; blend with a fork until all flour is moistened.
Makes 2 double pie crusts.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix butter, sour cream and egg together.
Add Bisquick.
Mix well.
Fill well-greased muffin tin about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: one meal sandwich(from richard simmons' show)
directions: Saute onion, garlic, salt, pepper, nutmeg and hamburger together.
When almost done, add your choice of greens.
Stir and cook until wilted.

title: lahvosh snack
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in dry Italian Good Seasons and Parmesan cheese.
Brush on each cracker.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes. Cool and break crackers for serving.

title: spiced ice tea
directions: Put sugar, water, nutmeg and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add the orange (stud the orange with whole cloves). Cover.
Cool and strain.
Add the orange juice, lemon juice and iced tea.
Serve over ice cubes in a tall glass.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter together, then add flour, meal, eggs and milk.
Add lemon juice.
Cook at 325° in uncooked pie shell until done.

title: luau mayonnaise
directions: Blend together to a smooth pink color.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg; add buttermilk and onion, mixing well.
Stir into dry ingredients; drop by teaspoonful into hot grease at 375°.
Drain on paper towels, then serve while hot.
Makes 12 to 18 hush puppies.

title: banana surprise
directions: Slice bananas in 1/2 pieces.
Put toothpick in and dip each piece in sour cream, then in coconut.
Place on plate and serve.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt margarine in double boiler; add flour and blend well. Stir in 1 cup half and half and cook slowly until it thickens (thin to medium thickness). Add salt and pepper. Now stir in the hominy. Add chili peppers and grated onion. Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath cookie bars
directions: Spread crackers in sheet cake or jelly roll pan.
Cook sugar and margarine for two minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Spread over graham crackers.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Break up 4 to 6 regular size Hershey bars and spread over cookies as soon as they come out of the oven.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add potatoes and toss to coat well. Sprinkle chopped eggs on top. Cover and chill. Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: apple snack
directions: Core and slice up apple.
Spread with peanut butter.

title: hot buttered cider
directions: In a saucepan, heat cider, orange, honey and whole spices until bubbly.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour cider into heat-proof mugs, adding a cinnamon stick to each mug.
Add rum to each mug and top with pat of butter.

title: risotto (rice) milanese
directions: Cook onion, garlic and rice in olive oil slowly for about 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Season with basil, salt and pepper (if necessary) and add chicken broth to rice a little at a time, mixing constantly as the rice absorbs the liquid.
Add saffron. Cook about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and quite moist, but not mushy and soft.
Stir in cheese just before serving.
Serve with pork sausage.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Grease pan (be sure it is hot before putting mix in it).
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil; butter.
Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Combine sugars, sour cream, margarine, spices and orange peel.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly, to dissolve sugars.
Continue cooking to 232° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir to blend well.

title: oven ratatouille(light and healthy veggies)
directions: Cut eggplant in 1/2 x 2-inch slices.
Slice zucchini 1/2-inch thick. Quarter tomatoes. Stem, seed and thinly slice peppers.
In a 3 to 4-quart dish, mix eggplant, zucchini, tomatoes, peppers, onion, basil and oil. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake, stirring once or twice, until eggplant is very soft and only a thin layer of liquid remains (about 20 minutes) or drain liquid if too much remains.
Season with salt and pepper.
Can be cooled, refrigerated up to 1 week and brought back to room temperature to reheat.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
When completely cool, crack into small pieces.
Put into large plastic bag with small amount of powdered sugar.
Shake to coat.

title: lo-cal eclairs
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 4 graham cracker squares in the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Pour on one half of the mixture.
Place on top of that 4 more crackers and the remaining pudding.
Top with the last 4 crackers. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.
Just before serving, pour in 1/4 teaspoon chocolate syrup.
Makes four servings.
Each serving equals 1 bread, 1/2 milk and 50 calories.

title: hot fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Stir in the milk and cook over low heat.
Blend in butter and continue to cook until you reach desired consistency.
Recipe makes 1 cup.
It can be frozen.

title: sauteed cabbage with kielbasa
directions: In a large pan, place olive oil and heat. Saute onion, cut in half and thinly sliced, until soft. Add cabbage, slivered with knife, tossing for 1 to 2 minutes. Add carrots which are shredded. Toss in pan 1 minute. Add turkey kielbasa, cut in pieces.
Add apple, cored and sliced.
Add seasonings. Add boiling water. Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer. Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chop walnuts into bite size pieces.
Slice bananas.
Dice apples bite size.
Peel and section oranges.
Dice into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients with fruit cocktail and liquid. Let sit in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scallops in casserole
directions: Saute scallops in 3 tablespoons butter until golden brown. Add white wine, stirring well.
Transfer mixture to buttered casserole.
Saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until soft, not browned.
Add to casserole with scallops.

title: baked autumn ham
directions: Bake ham in shallow baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven, set oven to 400°.
Place orange slices, pineapple slices, and sweet potatoes around ham.
Pour corn syrup and brown sugar over ham, orange, pineapple, and sweet potatoes. Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until browned and glazed. Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma jackson's angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well. Biscuits do not rise before baking.
Bake at 400° to 450° until brown.
Unused dough will keep up to a week in the refrigerator if well covered.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, add lemon juice and cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Whip Milnot and add to Jell-O mixture.
Crush crackers into fine crumbs, add melted margarine and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom and up sides.
Add filling and chill several hours.
You can save some of the crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish over the bottom.

title: freezer pickles
directions: In a large bowl (not metal), mix cucumbers, onion and salt. Cover and let stand in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over pickles.
Place in containers and evenly divide the liquid among the containers. Freeze.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Shake flour in bag.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag. Add chicken and green pepper to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce. Arrange chicken into an even layer. Close bag and cut slits in top.
Bake until tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve over your favorite cooked pasta.

title: easy does it chicken
directions: Place dried beef in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Wrap 2 slices bacon around each chicken breast.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix mushroom and chicken soup together.
Pour over casserole.
Cook 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Do not add salt.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients together; bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand for 12 hours.
Will keep indefinitely.
Serves 20.

title: cola roast
directions: Brown unseasoned roast in frying pan.
Place in foil lined pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour in cola drink. Cover and seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° until tender.
Time will vary with size of roast.
A 4 pound roast will take 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: ice cream pudding cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: barbecue sauce(1 cup)
directions: *Dip up all the molasses you can get on a teaspoon.

title: banana bread
directions: Butter pan and sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar and nuts in pan. Mix remaining dry ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly. Add milk, vanilla, butter, bananas and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until sides move away from pan.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add all ingredients to baked beans in a large ovenproof dish and bake for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Assemble ingredients in the following order:
Cook cornbread, enough to break up about 1-inch in bottom of your Pyrex dish. Next the pinto beans and crumble the bacon over the beans.
Mix the bell pepper and onion together and spread on top of the bacon. Spread the tomatoes on top of the onion and pepper.
Stir together the mayonnaise and pickle juice and blend in blender. Pour over the top of all the ingredients.
Use a fork and lightly work down the mayonnaise mixture into the ingredients.

title: oven fried mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In plastic bag, combine flour and paprika.
In another plastic bag, combine crumbs, cheese and basil.
In small bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Shake mushrooms in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture.
Shake in crumb mixture, pressing crumb mixture to mushrooms to coat.
Arrange mushrooms, cap side down, on prepared jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop green onions and shrimp
Mix everything together, except cheese.
Chill.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Place in loaf pan and top with tomato sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks in strips about
inches
long
by
1 inch wide. Pound meat.
Brush	with soy sauce, sprinkle with flour and salt. Brown in Wesson
oil
over	medium heat.
Add green peppers and water.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to persimmon pulp, buttermilk and eggs. Add butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for around 30 minutes or until done.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
To sausage grease add flour and brown.
Add sauteed vegetables, bay leaves, garlic, cayenne pepper, thyme, tomatoes, tomato paste, rice and beef stock.
Cook until the rice is done.

title: quick pickles
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar; pour over pickles and chill.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with buttered cheese Ritz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts until completely cooked.
Set aside (in warm oven).
Heat lemon juice on medium-high heat until slightly brown.
Add heavy cream.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and slowly add butter and 4 tablespoons sugar (still stirring constantly).
When sauce begins to slightly thicken, add roux and continue stirring until reduced by 1/4 to 1/2.
Remove from heat and serve over chicken immediately.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Beat together milk, vinegar, egg and mustard.
Pour over broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.

title: chicken picante
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chicken with garlic salt and pepper. Spread rice in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
In a small bowl, stir together broth, picante sauce, tomato sauce, onion and bell pepper.
Pour mixture over chicken. Bake, covered, 55 to 60 minutes at 350°. Uncover and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Pour Karo syrup on top.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach, pressing out water.
Mix with sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crumbs. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated and bread crumbs golden brown.

title: lettuce overnight salad
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Layer first 6 ingredients.
Spread salad dressing over the top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: frank's pan-bronzed cabbage
directions: Start off by cutting the cabbage into quarters and removing the "core" at the base of the head.
Then shred each section to the consistency of cole slaw and set it aside for a moment.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts.
Stir well and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Layer 4 enchilada shells on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix together all of the remaining ingredients (except cheese) in a mixing bowl. Spoon in half of the meat mixture and sprinkle on half of the cheese.
Trim off excess enchilada shells.
Repeat with remaining shells, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown choplets in margarine; add mushrooms and onion.
Cook until tender; add Vegex cube and water.
Heat just to boiling. Blend sour cream and flour and stir into broth.
Salt to taste. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (sauce will be thin). Serve over buttered noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Sift soda, salt and flour.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Add apples, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for one hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Leave oven closed until done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and sherry and set aside.
In a large saucepan, dissolve bouillon in the chicken broth over high heat. Add the beans and simmer until nearly all liquid has evaporated, about 5 to 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Drain the beans and set aside.

title: fudgy mint cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate with 1/2 cup margarine. In bowl, combine chocolate mixture with sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla and flour.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, 2 tablespoons margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk, then remaining ingredients.
Pour over brownie layer.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Top with glaze and cool.
Chill, then cut into bars.

title: breaded summer squash
directions: For any amount of sweet potatoes. Choose size of potatoes as close to the same size as possible as the larger and thicker one will take
longer to bake.

title: easy holiday mints
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Knead mixture until smooth.
Shape mints in candy mold or by shaping by hand. Place on cookie sheet; cover with paper towel.
Let dry.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with milk, mustard and salt in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Bake for 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mini sausage quiches
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese in medium bowl until creamy. Blend in flour, refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into 24 (1-inch) balls and press each into mini muffin cups.
Preheat oven to 375°. To prepare filing, crumble sausage into small skillet.
Cook
until browned.
Drain off any drippings.
Sprinkle evenly into pastry shells, sprinkle with cheese and chives.
Whisk eggs, half and half, salt and pepper until blended. Pour over sausage in pastry shells.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: honey orange dressing
directions: Blend dressing ingredients.
Makes approximately 1 cup.
Makes flavorful dressing on fruit or vegetable salad.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix together and enjoy.

title: fig preserves
directions: Put figs in a heavy pot and cover with sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Stir well next morning, bring to a boil and cook on medium heat until thick, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour hot into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well with beaters. Serve with all fruits.

title: glazed peanut butter balls
directions: Dip
balls
in
mixture with tongs.
Lay on waxed paper and let cool.
(Divide
cake of parseal to accommodate both 12 ounce chocolate and 6 ounce butterscotch morsels.)

title: stack cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add milk and margarine. Continue to mix batter together.
Stir in flour, adding a little at a time and continue to beat batter.
Add cinnamon to batter and keep adding flour until dough is stiff in the bowl.
On a floured surface, divide the dough into small balls.
I generally have enough dough to make 2 cakes, a 9-inch and an 8-inch one. Grease and flour pans generously.
Shake out any remaining flour.
Place one small ball in the pan and pat out gently to the edge of the pan.
Layer should be very thin or you will have a very thick layer when it bakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Put everything in large bowl and stir well.
Put into extra large baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hrs.

title: hashbrown casserole
directions: Spray baking dish sides with Pam for easier cleanup.
Melt margarine and pour in baking dish.
Add hashbrowns.
Add diced onions on top of potatoes.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together and pour over potatoes.
Spread grated Cheddar cheese next.
Mix corn flakes and melted margarine together and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: good and spicy meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine crushed corn flakes, catsup and egg.
Mix in ground beef.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch meatballs. Place in single layer in greased or foil lined shallow baking pan. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes or until browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 2 loaf pans 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped corn and tomatoes
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and fold in sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour warm water in mixing bowl.
Add, stirring, to dissolve dry yeast.
Stir in sugar, salt, soft shortening and egg.
Mix in with hands until dough is easy to handle sifted flour.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place rounded dough in greased bowl; cover with a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator (can be left overnight).

title: hermits
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in coffee. Stir dry ingredients together, blend into shortening mixture.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly in center.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: deluxe chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt and spread liberally with Dijon mustard, covering completely.
Dip chicken pieces into bread crumbs and place in baking pan oiled with olive oil.
Melt butter and drizzle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour.
Pound in with meat mallet.
Turn meat and pound in remaining flour.
Cut meat into 6 to 8 serving pieces.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meat in shortening over medium heat, about 15 minutes. Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Mix water and soup; pour over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender. Place meat on warm platter.
Heat remaining gravy mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eight hour chili
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet. Transfer to a 4 quart slow cooker. Stir in the rest of the ingredients; mix well. Cover and cook at low setting for 8 - 10 hours or on high for 5 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add bananas.
Mix well.
Combine flour and other dry ingredients in another bowl.
Add flour mixture 1/2 at a time, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix in pecans.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Cut with cutter.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat and cook at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add walnuts.
In bowl beat egg and add applesauce and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour in greased pan 8 x 4 x 4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook on rack.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add onion.
Saute for 3 minutes. Add broth.
Heat until boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Gradually add noodles.
Continue to boil.
Cook uncovered for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes or longer if using fresh broccoli.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add more milk if soup is too thick.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Cook corn meal and 2 cups milk until consistency of mush. Remove from heat.
Add salt, baking powder, shortening and remaining 1 cup of milk.
Add egg yolks and fold in egg whites. Bake in greased two-quart baking dish in moderate oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Spoon into warm dishes; top with butter.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Break or chop lettuce in small pieces.
Add undrained shrimp, chopped onions and the juice of the lemons and the oil.
Toss and chill.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: In small bowl, mix first 5 ingredients; fold in whipped cream. Serve on roast, broiled beef, baked ham, corned beef or fried or poached fish.

title: depression plant
directions: Put several pieces of coal or charcoal in deep dish (glass) or fishbowl.
Around the coal, but not on top of it, pour water, salt, household blueing, ammonia and iodine or red ink.
Do not stir these ingredients or move bowl anymore than necessary.
In few days, beautiful, mossy crystal growth will appear.
For a week or 2 add salt and water as the liquid disappears.
After the crystals cover coal completely, you needn't add any more water.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix remaining ingredients with 1 cup water and simmer until meat is fork-tender. Add extra water as needed.
Thicken stew with cornstarch that has been mixed with water (little).
Serve with rice or egg noodles.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and shortening in water.
Stir in 4 cups flour, salt and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Put into a greased bowl, turn to coat.
Cover with double thickness of plastic wrap to rise. Punch dough down every 10 minutes for the first hour.
Let rise for 1 hour more or until doubled.
Punch down.
Rest 10 minutes. Divide dough into loaves, 2 large or 4 small.
Place on greased cookie sheets or 9 x 5-inch bread pans.
Slash tops.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Brush warm loaves with melted butter.

title: prune cake
directions: Stir in a saucepan, sugar, buttermilk (in which soda has been added), white syrup, butter and vanilla.
Boil about 1 minute and pour over cake while still warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; pour in bottom of casserole dish.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces (add next).
Cut up eggs (add next).
Cut up onion (add next).
Mix soup and milk together in separate bowl (add).
Mix 2 cups of hot water bouillon or chicken broth together with dressing mix.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and vegetable casserole
directions: Place unthawed vegetables in center of baking dish; surround with rice and pimiento and dot with butter.
Salt and pepper.
Add water.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Check rice to see if more water is needed.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: gram's icing
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients well.
Add flour, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in buttered square baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Mix together orange juice, ginger and allspice.
Pour over chicken and bake for 1/2 hour more, basting twice.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, sugar and vinegar.
Beat egg and add.
Blend well and cook until thick.
Cool.
Then add rest of ingredients and fold in whipped topping.
Chill to set.
You may cook the mixture a day ahead of time.

title: lemon-pineapple delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water in bowl.
Add ice cream; mix until melted.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Chill until set.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate mint thumbprints(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in the vanilla.
Sift flour and cocoa.
Stir into the creamed mixture. Stir in chopped nuts.
Chill the dough 30 minutes.

title: harvest squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with 1 small bag of stuffing and 1/2 cup water.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and add dressing and seasoning.

title: super hamburger stew
directions: Cook in Dutch oven until done the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining.
Cover and cook on low for 1 hour or until carrots are done.
Serve with rice or hot corn bread.

title: quick and easy brown gravy
directions: Combine water, flour and coffee in shaker.
Heat grease drippings and add water and flour mixture.
Cook at medium heat. Stir constantly.
Add salt and chopped onions.
Let simmer.
Season to taste.

title: molasses bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. For added moisture, pour on cake syrup made from 1/4 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs, then add dry ingredients and lastly add vanilla, fruit and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
Can be stored in refrigerator and baked as needed.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Stir together 1 cup
sugar
and
cornstarch in saucepan. Gradually
stir
in water until
smooth.
Stir
in
egg
yolks, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir
in
lemon
rind,
juice
and margarine.
Cool.
Turn in baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add 1/3 cup
sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating after each.
Beat until stiff.
Spread on pie and bake. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in a double boiler and pour mixture over package of gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese until dissolved and add crushed pineapple.
Let cool. Blend in whipping cream and mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix half and half, milk and cheese; heat until cheese melts. Stir-fry onions, celery and carrots in butter; then add flour and broth.

title: bacon hors d'oeuvres
directions: Leave bacon out all day to soften.
Cut each slice in half. Wrap a half slice around a cracker, making sure ends are on bottom.
Place on rack on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until crisp.

title: vegetable primavera
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon of the chicken broth, the mustard, olive oil and vinegar; set aside

title: chicken glaze
directions: Melt butter and add ingredients.
Glaze your chicken pieces. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cherry topped cheesecake pie
directions: Combine these ingredients; mix well.
Press into bottom and side of 8-inch pie pan.
chill.

title: chewy gooey cake
directions: Mix egg, cake mix and butter together.
If too stiff, add water and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with a mixture of the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs; mix together until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size pan.
Whisk until smooth. Turn burner on medium heat. Stir constantly. When it starts "sticking" it's almost ready. Remove from heat and drop the whole lump on wax paper.
Knead a few times.
Store in plastic Ziploc bag.

title: creamed beans and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; cover with water and cook until tender.
Cook beans according to package directions.

title: mississippi shrimp-crab-okra gumbo
directions: Mix peeled and deveined shrimp with crabmeat.
Make roux (dark) of flour and oil.
Add shrimp, crab and okra, stirring for a few minutes constantly.
Set aside.

title: special k bars(easy and all ages love 'em!)
directions: In a large pan, bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add Special K, coating thoroughly.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
In either a double boiler or microwave, melt the chocolate and butterscotch morsels together.
Spread melted morsels over bar mixture.
Cut and serve.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients and then add the remainder of ingredients.
Blend well, then pour into prepared pastry lined pie plate and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break crackers into 4 oblong pieces and place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle pecans over crackers.
Melt margarine, butter and sugar.
Boil 2 minutes exactly, stirring continuously.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes.
Take up immediately and place on aluminum foil.
After cooling, store in airtight container.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour and vanilla. Make into small balls.
Press dent in center.
Fill with currant jelly.
Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Prepare tube pan by oiling and dusting with flour.
Place chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Blend cake mix, Jell-O, wine and eggs at medium speed until ingredients are well blended (approximately 2 minutes).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Fix rice as directed on box.
After rice has set as directed; mix in other ingredients.
Put in airtight Tupperware container and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: beans presbyterian
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix in other ingredients in large casserole. Heat to serve.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Core and slice apples (do not peel).
Add only enough water to cook until soft.
Put through a ricer or fine sieve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Lower heat and simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking. Can be refrigerated for up to one month.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O according to directions on box; pour into large dish and let stand until thickened.
For filling, mix together lemon Jell-O, 1 cup water, cream cheese, pineapple, celery, nuts and whipping cream.
Pour over hardened lime Jell-O until thickened.
Prepare cherry Jell-O as directed on box and pour over filling.
Let thicken.
Yields 20 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all ingredients except Cool Whip until fluffy.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and zucchini; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.
They freeze well.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain well, then add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cook for 2 hours on simmer.
Cook spaghetti.
In a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan, layer sauce, spaghetti and cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Make sure cheese is on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, then let sit for 10 to 15 minutes to set up.
Cut into squares.

title: "for the birds" suet cake
directions: Combine ingredients, adding more peanut butter if needed to hold mixture together.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls. Serve in a net bag (like onions come in) or 1/2 grapefruit rind with strings to hang in tree.

title: under sea salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1
1/2 cups hot water and 1/2 cup pear juice.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 mixture in pan and let set.
Utilizing rest of Jello as it congeals, whip until it thickens and is fluffy.
Work cheese and ginger into the mix with whipped Jello and fork in pears last.
Fold on "sea".

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Remove outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut in 6 or 8 wedges and place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Arrange the onions, beef and rice between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Pour over contents and cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: glorified scrambled eggs
directions: Beat ingredients with beater until mixed real good.
Cook in small amount of oil in frypan, scrambling together.
Delicious!

title: country beef curry
directions: Cut beef into 1/2-inch cubes.
Shake in a bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a skillet and brown beef.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic to skillet and cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add curry powder and cook for 2 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes and water; mix well. Place meat into a casserole and pour sauce over it.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add raisins and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla in saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream or cake. Yields 1 1/2 cups.
May be stored tightly covered in refrigerator and reheated as needed.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season with taste of 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Follow advice of Solomon in Proverbs 23:14 (first three words).

title: ripe tomato ketchup
directions: Wash and peel tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes, onions and pepper. Combine all ingredients in large pan; cook until thick.
This can be waterbathed in cans or frozen.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in flat baking dish.
Lay turkey or chicken pieces on top.
In a separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sherry and curry powder.
Pour over meat slices.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: wendy's dilled macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, omitting salt; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Combine remaining ingredients; gently stir into macaroni.
Chill 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sinful trifle
directions: Cut cake into small squares and place half of cake into a large glass bowl.
Prepare each box of pudding with 1 2/3 cups milk. Add 1/2 teaspoon liqueur or extract to each.
Spoon one pudding over cake. Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Crunch 2 bars of candy over Cool Whip. Repeat layering, ending with candy. Refrigerate.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with fresh fruit.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery.
Drain. Mix in mushrooms and peas.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Put mixture in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add brown gravy and mix together. Frost with approximately 1 inch of mashed potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°, uncovered.
Ten minutes prior to being done, sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese and return to oven.

title: berry marble cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; stir in milk, vanilla and butter.
Spread batter thin in 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Scatter berries (blueberries or blackberries) over batter.
Sprinkle sugar over berries and pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well browned and done.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: whiskey sour
directions: Be sure you use the same size can when measuring.

title: old fashion dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, cornbread, biscuits, salt, pepper, sage and chicken broth.
Make it moist (not too soupie).
Cook in light greased pan at 350° until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs with butter.
Form in a 9-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour the water in a saucepan and sprinkle gelatin over it.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Stir to blend.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens.
Do not boil!
Remove from heat.
Stir the liqueurs into the mixture, then chill until mixture starts to mound slightly.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Spread 1/2 of cabbage in oblong baking dish.
Layer ingredients in order given, adding other half of cabbage on top. Pour sauce over all.
Bake 50 minutes in 400° oven.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatine-cold water mixture in the cup of hot water, then add the mayonnaise, corned beef, celery, onion and green pepper.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in pie crusts.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large frypan, brown chicken in butter.
In casserole dish, mix sour cream, soup and mushrooms. When chicken is lightly browned, place mixture in casserole dish. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes (until chicken is done).
Serve over rice.

title: "fruit pizza"
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip together well.
Put this mixture on baked crust.
Next, put the fruit pie filling on top and refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Rinse chicken well.
Cook in water to cover in large saucepan until tender.
Drain and bone chicken, reserving broth.
Cook onion and green pepper in broth in saucepan until tender.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until tender; drain.
Add chicken, tomatoes, soups, pimentos, mushrooms, Velveeta and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Cook until Velveeta melts.
Spoon into two 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This will make 18 to 24 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine everything but soup, Knox gelatine and water. Heat soup, then add dissolved gelatine to it.
Add this to the other combined ingredients. Pour into a mold and chill for at least 8 hours.
(Works good in small Tupperware mold.)

title: do nothing cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, soda and salt, then add pineapple.
Mix in flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in long cake pan.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers; when cool, split layers, making 4 layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar and 1 package frozen coconut, thawed.
Spread between layers.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and cook about 5 minutes, drain and set aside. Mix milk, mayonnaise, soup, cheddar cheese, add salt and pepper, pour over cabbage.
Mix stick margarine and crushed cornflakes. Put half on bottom of pan, then other half on top.
Bake 350 for 25 minutes.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar; blend in milk and flavoring.
Stir in flour, chopped candies and chopped pecans. Form dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Roll in flaked coconut to coat outside.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until edges are golden, 12 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cube.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
In separate bowl, melt butter and mix with crackers and poppy seed.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of cracker mixture. Spoon in all of chicken mixture.
Layer remaining poppy seed mix. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat to soft ball.
Cool. Beat until thick.
Add vanilla and nuts while beating, then pour in buttered glass pan.

title: beef rolls
directions: Spread cream cheese on sliced beef.
Cut onion to length of sliced beef.
Place in the middle and roll up.

title: spiced cider bowl
directions: Do Ahead:
In a 6-quart kettle, bring all ingredients, except apples, to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Strain through double layer of cheesecloth.
Refrigerate cider until needed.

title: baked potato slices
directions: Melt butter in large casserole in microwave.
Add soup, salt and water.
Slice in potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese quiche squares
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Stir flour, baking powder, salt together; stir into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased 13x9 pan.
Bake about 45 min. until set. Let cool 15 min.; cut into squares.
Yield:
24-2 in. squares.

title: toasted onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.
Can be used with chips or with vegetables.

title: persimmon candy
directions: Mix up well; shape into rolls.
Put in freezer; cut in slices.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Bring salted water to a boil. Add shrimp. When it comes to second boil, remove from heat. Cool shrimp under cold water. Drain. Mix together eggs, cream, cheese and salt. Slowly cook onions in butter until soft. Add to egg mixture along with chives, marjoram, parsley and cooked shrimp. Spoon into pastry shell. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cajun baked haddock
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine Cajun seasoning, garlic powder and paprika in a shallow dish.
Spread oil over haddock, then roll in spices until evenly coated.
Place fish in a baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness or when fish is flaky and tender.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix 3/4 cup crumbs with melted butter; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with the buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: dilly bread(from weight watchers cookbook)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour.
Add 4 1/4 cups of the flour, one cup at a time, stirring with wooden spoon after each addition, until soft dough forms.
Sprinkle work surface with 2 tablespoons of the remaining flour.
Turn dough out onto floured surface.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Drain crushed pineapple.
Pour juice to measure 1 1/8 cups. Heat to boiling.
Stir into gelatin and add crushed pineapple. Cool.
When it begins to set, stir in cantaloupe and peach slices. Chill about 4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: butterscotch crunchers
directions: Cover a baking sheet with wax paper.
Open can of noodles.
Add noodles, cereal, peanuts, marshmallows and raisins in a large mixing bowl; stir.
Measure peanut butter, set aside.
Melt butterscotch in double boiler, add peanut butter to butterscotch. Do not cover.
Place in microwave, set on 100% power.
Set time for 1 minute and 15 seconds.
Push start button.
Stir a couple of times.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Stir until pieces are coated. Drop on wax paper and chill.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer as listed in a large casserole dish or cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread johnnycake
directions: (Uses no shortening and no eggs.)
Grease an 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Bake at 375° about 23 minutes.
This is a moist corn bread.

title: potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a 10-inch gratin dish or glass pie plate with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Layer 1/3 of the potatoes over the bottom of the prepared gratin dish or pie plate, overlapping the slices in a spiral pattern.
Over the potatoes, sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the flour and arrange the onion rings. Dust with the cayenne pepper and 1/2 teaspoon paprika.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: *Substitute:
Spray pan lightly with nonstick cooking spray and replace oil with 2 tablespoons water.

title: norma's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef until it loses its color.
Add onion, celery and garlic, cooking briefly at low heat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chili cheese taco dip
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Pour all ingredients into crock pot until cheese is melted.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook together the chili powder, onion, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Crush tortilla chips; put in bottom of casserole dish. Dampen the chips with 1/2 cup broth.
Put half of chicken on the tortillas; cover with half of the soup mixture.
Make a second layer.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: unbaked fudge clusters
directions: Heat butter and milk.
Add sugar and cocoa; boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Next, add the peanut butter, vanilla and uncooked oatmeal; stir until blended.
Drop the mixture by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Let stand for 30 minutes, or until firm, then enjoy!!!

title: healthy pasta
directions: Puree all but tomatoes.
Process tomatoes only to chunky stage.
Pour over fresh cooked angel hair or fettucini.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap each quarter apple in roll and place in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and heat until hot. Pour over rolls and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Use fresh or freeze and add chunks to soups, stews or pasta.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tight container.
Do not refrigerate.
Serve 2 teaspoons mixed with boiling water.

title: easiest and best lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat spaghetti sauce and water in a saucepan.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, Parmesan and parsley.

Pour 3/4 cup sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam); arrange 1/3 of the uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce. Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with half the cheese mixture and cover cheese with half the meat.
Cover all with 1/2 cup sauce.
Repeat the layers and top with remaining pasta and sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peppermint canes
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, margarine and sugar with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Beat in egg and peppermint extract. Stir in flour until blended.
If dough is too soft to hold shape, chill 15 to 30 minutes.
Using a pastry bag fitted with plain #4 tube, pipe dough in 4-inch cane shapes, 1 inch apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are light golden.
Remove to rack to cool.
Decorate with icing.
Store airtight.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Blend until mixed.
Great on grilled chicken sandwiches or with chicken nuggets.

title: strawberry daiquiri slush
directions: Mix ingredients in blender; freeze. Add 7-Up when you serve.

title: 3 layer orange bars
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and flour and press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cover crust with orange slices (while hot).
Mix eggs, flour, baking powder, coconut and nuts.
Pour over orange slices and spread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar until light and fluffy. Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; stir into butter mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan.
Spoon rhubarb over batter.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar over rhubarb.
Pour fruit juice over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour cocoa, salt and baking powder in small bowl.
In large bowl cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Add one egg at a time to mixture.
Cream after each addition. Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to the butter mixture. Add vanilla.
Bake in 9x15 inch or Bundt pan at 325 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: preacher cookies with no chocolate
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and milk 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
These are a little more gooey and may need to add a little more oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chicken sumi salad
directions: Remove flavor packet from Top Ramen package and reserve for dressing.
Crush Top Ramen noodles in 1/2 inch pieces, set aside. Toss together the cabbage, green onions, almonds, sesame seed and chicken.
Add noodles and toss again.
Just before serving, add dressing and toss.
Makes 10 servings.

title: andy's best-ever sloppy joes
directions: Mix all together and simmer in a slow cooker until serving time.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cook chili sauce and grape jelly in crock-pot.
Add hot dogs; cook about 30 minutes.

title: potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes with eggs and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Form into flat cakes and cook slowly on a hot griddle.
Makes about 10.
Served with sausage these make an old-fashioned supper.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, 1 egg, vanilla, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 1/4 cups pecans.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread in pie shell.

title: texas eggs
directions: Beat eggs with milk and butter.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle vegetables and bacon onto eggs.
Heat soup (do not add milk or water) to soften it.
Spread over egg dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 12 minutes at 420 degrees. Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and transfer to pie shell. Cook in micro-convection oven at 350 degrees for 12 minutes. Let stand in oven for 5-10 minutes, or cook 30-40 minutes in regular oven at 350 degrees.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In large skillet, combine oil, onion soup mix, water, onion, pepper, mushrooms, vegetables, salt and pepper (to taste).
Stir to mix well.
Bring to boil; stir frequently.
Simmer until done and water is almost evaporated. Sprinkle with a touch of soy sauce.
Serve with rice of your choice.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To make sauce, cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thickened and bubbly.
Layer 1/2 potatoes and pour half sauce over and repeat layers and remainder of sauce.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes, stirring once. Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are cooked.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Grate cheese.
With your hands, mix all ingredients together except olives.
Roll a small piece of dough and shape around each olive.
Freeze.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Recipe doubles easily.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and margarine. Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix well until light and fluffy. Spread this on the two crusts.
Chill.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Blend
in the well drained pineapple and nuts. Spoon on top of the sugar-margarine mixture and chill again.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all together and let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Mix ingredients.
Spread in pan. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix brown sugar, cream, caramel flavoring and butter in saucepan over medium heat.
When all ingredients are dissolved and start to boil, mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Add to mixture when thickened.
Take off heat.
Spread on cake.

title: lo-cal cheese 'n vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix lightly.
Add eggs; mix well.
Coat a casserole dish with melted margarine.
Add vegetable mixture; bake for 1 hour, until top is brown and crisp.
Serve topped with a dollop of yogurt.
Each serving contains approximately 153 calories.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash and dry seeds.
Mix with oil and salt.
Put on flat baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until crisp. Stir occasionally.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend milk, butter and rice together. Heat slowly until scalded.
Mix sugar, raisins, vanilla and eggs. Combine with hot rice mixture and pour into buttered baking dish. Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour.

title: garlic soup
directions: Open the broth and garbanzos and uncap the olive oil.
Get a pot large enough to accommodate the contents of the 3 cans plus the macaroni.
Slice the garlic thin or chop it into small pieces. Pour enough olive oil into the pan to amply cover the bottom.
Turn the heat to medium (halfway between high and low if you don't have an indicator).
When oil is hot drop in the garlic.
Watch it so it does not get burned.
When the garlic is brown, pour in both cans of broth.
Turn the heat up a bit and bring the broth to a boil; now drop in 6 ounces of the macaroni and stir a couple of times after it goes in.
When macaroni is done (following instructions on the package) about 10 minutes, then pour in the garbanzos, liquid and all.
When the soup comes to a boil. turn off the heat.

title: tinka buttermilk cake
directions: Bring ingredients to room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Keep batter well creamed.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Do not over or underbeat.
Put in lightly floured and greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: brown bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured pan.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into square pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining sugar, brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter. Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top. Garnish as desired.
Cool Whip or whipped cream is good.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Bake in muffin pans.
May keep in refrigerator 6 weeks and bake as needed. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream first 3
ingredients
until fluffy.
Combine soda and flour.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and bananas. Stir in floured nuts (and
coconut).
Bake
in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° until brown.
Leave plain or ice with caramel or cream cheese frosting.
Also bakes well in a Bundt pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Add a good 1/2 box of Stove Top dressing mix to chicken and melted oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use the rest of the Stove Top dressing on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off the fat.
Mix in the tomato sauce, taco mix and soup.
Layer the tortillas, meat mixture and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Repeat the layers until the meat mixture runs out.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted, about 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown meats together and drain well.
Melt Velveeta into the meats.
Add the following:
basil, oregano, parsley and garlic powder/salt.
Spread mixture onto party rye bread slices.
Heat in microwave or in oven on 350° until spread is bubbly.
(Mixture freezes well.)

title: oui goui cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo and 1 egg; pat into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, vanilla, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 38 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken-broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine per package directions.
Add broccoli last 4 minutes.
Drain.
In skillet over medium-high heat melt butter. Add chicken and cook till brown.
Stir often.
Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and noodles.
Mix and cook through, stirring often.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Place oyster crackers in brown paper bag.
Mix other ingredients and pour over crackers.
Shake and let stand two hours, occasionally shaking during the two hour period.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1-quart measuring cup.
Microwave at High 1/2 minute, or until melted.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Layer half of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving. May top with shredded sharp cheese.
Cheese melts as casserole stands.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas bread
directions: Scald milk, then cool.
Dissolve yeast cake in water and add to cooled milk.
Add sugar and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat well and let rise in warm place until double in bulk and light and bubbly (about 1 hour).
Cream together shortening, sugar, salt and eggs and beat well.
Put two mixtures together and mix well.
Add remaining flour, chopped nuts and finely cut fruits mixed together.
Mix well and brush with melted shortening.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
