Shape into buns, rings or loaves and place in greased pans.
Let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with thin powdered sugar frosting while still warm.
Makes about 3 loaves.

title: baked swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top each chicken breast with cheese slice.
Combine soup and wine, mixing well. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing, Drizzle butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Chicken can be prepared ahead, then baked just before serving.

title: quick apple dumplings
directions: Mix biscuit mix and milk according to directions.
Roll thin. Spread with butter.
Leave on board.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well on medium speed of mixer.
Blend in applesauce.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add soda solution alternately with dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Blend on low speed of mixer.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased and lightly floured 9 x 11-inch pan.
Frost when cool with cream cheese frosting.

title: omelette extraordinaire
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Beat combined egg yolks and milk until thick and lemon colored. Fold into egg whites. Melt butter in 10-inch ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Add egg mixture; cook 3 minutes or until underside is golden brown. Bake in 325° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Remove from oven. Make a deep crease across center of top of omelette. Place cheese, mushrooms and peppers on half of omelette; continue baking until cheese begins to melt. Slip spatula underneath; tip skillet to loosen and gently fold in half. Makes 4 servings.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into strips.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil, using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender.
Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak. Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch in microwave, stopping and stirring every few minutes.
After it has thickened, add vanilla. Add peach jello for color.
Mix with peaches and pour in pie shells.
Let cool and cover with Cool Whip.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken wings.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight, turning wings once.
Bake, uncovered, on cookie sheet.
Pour excess marinade over wings. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken kelly
directions: Cook and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Marinate in beaten eggs for 2 hours.
Mix bread crumbs, garlic powder and parsley in bag.
Add chicken and shake until coated.
Brown chicken in oil.
Drain on towel.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add chicken, layer of drained mushrooms and cover with cheese.
Pour broth over mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: carmine's lobster newburg
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Cook like for gravy.
Add cream 1/3 at a time.
Add wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Add paprika for color.
Let thicken.
Add lobster to sauce.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the top browns.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tasha's chili
directions: Saute onion, carrots and chili peppers.
Add to browned ground beef.
Add chili powder.
Pour in tomato juice.
Add rice and heat through.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing, onion soup mix and parsley.
Cover; chill until serving time. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crinkle cookies
directions: Mix the cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together; make balls or spoon cookies.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: white gravy
directions: Heat grease until hot; add flour and stir.
When flour has become brown, add milk.
Stir until soupy.

title: tripe stew
directions: In a pot, add oil, onions, cilantro, black pepper, tomato, garlic, salt, green pepper, cumin and oregano.
Add potatoes and tripe.
Add peanut butter (blended with milk).
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Add water as needed and cook until the potatoes are very soft.
Serve hot with avocado and tostados.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Chill all ingredients thoroughly before use, including flour. Cut the shortening into the flour until the shortening is marble sized.
Dissolve the salt in the ice water and then add to the flour-shortening mixture.
Mix just long enough to wet the flour; do not overmix.

title: lion's head meatballs
directions: Remove stems from bok choy; chop enough to measure 1 cup. Place leaves in
9 x 13 inch microwave-safe baking dish; add enough warm water to fill dish halfway.
Cover; microwave on High 5 minutes.
Remove leaves and cool with cold water; drain. Spread leaves out flat on paper towels; set aside. Thoroughly combine next 6 ingredients and bok choy stems.
Divide into 6 equal portions; shape into meatballs.
Enclose each in bok choy leaf; place in 9 x 13 inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover; microwave on
Medium-high (70%) 6 minutes.
Uncover; brush tops lightly with 1 Tbsp. stir-fry sauce.
Cover; microwave on Medium-high (70%) 7 minutes longer. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: feijoada(black beans and rice)
directions: Soak beans and soda overnight in enough water to cover.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
The next day, saute onion, celery and bell pepper in olive oil in a Dutch oven.
Brown meats together. Drain.
Add to onion mixture.
Add beans, then 3 quarts water. Bring to a boil.
Add remaining spices, stir well and let simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Boil noodles until tender; drain.
Place into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange tuna on top.
Sprinkle with pepper, lightly.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour over mixture.
Cover with chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: best whole-wheat bread
directions: Scald milk. Add shortening, sugar and salt. Stir until dissolved. Add whole-wheat flour and beat rapidly with spoon. Add yeast and cold water. Mix well, then add enough white flour to make a soft dough. Let rise until double. Punch down. Put in greased bowl. Let rise until double again. Shape into 3 loaves. Cover for 15 minutes. Spank real hard to take out air bubbles. Let rise and bake.

title: apple pie
directions: Stir together 1/4 pound of softened butter,
nutmeg, flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt with sliced apples.
Mix lightly.
Turn into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with remaining butter.
Top with crust. Slit.
Seal and flute.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove tinfoil the last 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape cookies as desired; dough may be chilled, rolled out and cut with cookie cutters or can be rolled into walnut sized balls and flattened with the greased bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into balls, flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10-12
minutes at 350°.

title: crab casserole with white sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and stir well, then cook until thick, stirring often.
Next, add spices.
Cool, add crackers and crabmeat.

title: florida punch
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1/2 of orange sherbet, orange juice, lime juice and sugar, stirring until sherbet has melted completely.
Pour milk into punch bowl.
Add fruit juice mixture. Stir well and float remaining scoops of sherbet on top.
Garnish with orange, lime slices and cherries.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and chocolate syrup until smooth. Fold in marshmallow cream. Cover and refrigerate until set.

title: pickled fish
directions: Cut fish in small pieces.
Soak in salt water (salty enough to float an egg).
Refrigerate for 48 hours.
Two days later, drain and soak in vinegar.
Refrigerate for 48 hours.
Two days later, drain off vinegar.

title: bacon blue cheese dip
directions: Fry bacon with garlic until crisp, drain and set aside.
Beat cream cheese, half & half and blue cheese. Stir in bacon, garlic and chives.
Place into a small casserole dish and bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with almonds and serve with crackers.
Keep warm over a candle warmer.

title: white beans - no gas
directions: Wash beans and place in a large pot; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover tightly and allow it to stand for 1 hour.
Drain; cover with water again and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until tender, adding the salt, ham hock or bacon after the first 30 minutes.

title: tuna cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Blend together soup and milk in saucepan.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Add to noodle mixture.
Serve with nuts mixed in or sprinkled on top.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat cooking oil in a large cook pot and brown onion and ground beef with garlic powder and parsley.
Drain grease and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and cook, uncovered, on low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked spaghetti. Top with your favorite cheese.

title: egg dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pan-fry sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard together.
Pour egg mixture over bread. Add sausage and grated cheese.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Press sausage and cheese into liquid.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You may also add onions, chopped ham, mushrooms and green peppers.

title: mimi's easy chocolate mousse
directions: Put milk into a saucepan and warm until very, very hot but not scalded.
Place rest of ingredients into blender and add hot milk. Blend for 2 minutes at high speed.
(Make sure it's 2 full minutes.)
Pour into wine glasses or parfaits.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar. Combine with rest of ingredients.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine yeast and 2 cups lukewarm water in a large bowl; let mixture stand 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and remaining ingredients until blended.
Spoon into well greased cast iron muffin pans, filling two-thirds full, or into well greased cast iron drop biscuit pans, filling half full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until rolls are golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop all ingredients and sprinkle on cheese.
Add m.s.g. and mix all ingredients together.
If desired, roll in chopped pecans.
Makes 2 balls.
Serve with Wheatsworth crackers.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute meats and onion together until done.
Cut tops from peppers and clean inside.
Fill with meat mixture.
Put on baking dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken with enough water to have 2 cups broth.
Mix soups with broth and onion until boiling.
Fix stuffing as directed on box using the margarine.
Put half of the dressing into the bottom of a rectangular casserole dish.
Remove chicken from bone and cube.
Place the chicken on top of dressing in pan. Pour soup mixture over chicken and then add remaining dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Cut and serve.

title: banana-oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2 inch) muffin pan cups. In large bowl mix on medium speed, beat butter and sugar until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1 tablespoon oats, beat about 1 minute until batter is smooth.
Spoon batter into muffin cups; sprinkle with remaining oats.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli after cooking. Grease dish lightly with Crisco. Place broccoli in dish uniformly.
Mix together mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
After mixing together, pour this over broccoli. Top broccoli casserole with 1/2 cup crushed Cheez-Its crackers.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Slow cook in crock-pot for 2 hours on high then 2 hours on low.
Great for holidays.

title: fajitas
directions: Dip chicken in mixture.
Sear over high heat, then grill until cooked, brush with mixture several times.
Slice in thin strips when done.
Wrap in flour tortilla with chopped onions, tomatoes, lettuce, grated cheese, sour cream and hot sauce.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Press into bottom of pan. Freeze until firm.
Spread ice cream over crust.
Drizzle chocolate over top.
Freeze until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into Bisquick, then mix into sausage.
Mix real well until it forms a ball.
Pinch off 1-inch balls and roll real solid.
Put on cookie sheet.
Stick in freezer for 10 minutes to make more solid.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Can freeze solid and keep in freezer until ready to use.
Makes about 100.

title: fake pineapple
directions: Remove peeling and seed from zucchini. Grate or dice.
Mix all ingredients well and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently. Pour mixture into clean jars and process 30 minutes in hot water bath.

title: lima bean and corn casserole
directions: Make white sauce using first 5 ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes after it thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and top with bread crumbs, mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 glass dish.
Spread undrained pineapple on bottom; add layer of blueberries and sugar. Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Drizzle melted oleo.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake 25 minutes; pierce, return and finish baking.

title: swiss mocha
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Process in a blender until powdered.
Use 2 tablespoons for each 4 ounce cup of hot water. Forty calories each.

title: quick baked beans(joey mostowy, bruin, pennsylvania)
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp; set aside. Saute garlic, onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until golden. Add beef. Brown well; drain. Season with salt and pepper, if desired. Stir in beans and hot dogs; cover and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes. Crumble bacon over top and serve. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix ground beef and soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with onion, then Tater Tots, then finish with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: delicious deluxe pound cake
directions: Let butter and Crisco come to room temperature.
Cream with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg is added.
Add flavoring.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° until cake is done, about 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Remove and add glaze.

title: grandma lena holland's canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix sugars, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a cast-iron Dutch oven.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Set on cooler part of wood stove.
Cook, stirring until thick, about 5 minutes.
Stir in juice.
Pack into jars 1/3 full with apple slices.
Pour in liquid until it covers apples.
Remove air bubbles.
Fill within 1-inch of top of jars and seal.
Cook in water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: valley mashed potatoes
directions: To 4 cups mashed potatoes, stir in salad dressing mix.
Add butter or margarine.
Do not add salt.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and stir to blend.
Do not beat.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan that has been greased and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
I use in place of a fruit cake.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Melt butter in medium size pot.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk and boil 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by tablespoons.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Whip these ingredients together until creamy.
Take fruit of your choice and add some to the mixture.
Fill a graham cracker crust with the mix and top with remaining fruit.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix onion, chicken broth, chicken, cheese and rice.
Cover, bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sand cups
directions: Pour
milk
into
large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with a wire
whisk
until
well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.	Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies. Place
1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups.
Fill cups
3/4 full
with	pudding
mixture.
Top	with
remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour; decorate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch casserole pan.
Combine other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: five-spice fried rice(serves 2)
directions: Cut beef in 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine sugar, five-spice powder and pepper flakes; coat beef cubes with spice mixture.
Heat oil and garlic in medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Brown beef in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir-fry until thoroughly heated.

title: fudge
directions: Melt ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until blended.
Stir in the coconut.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: sour cream poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Baker's Joy and dust with sugar. Blend together everything but the cake mix. Add cake mix. Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes. Bake for 45 minutes or longer at 325°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain and chill for 1 hour.
Combine and blend well all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add chilled macaroni and mix well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: arlene's burritos
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until hamburger is crumbly; drain fat.
Add refried beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Grate cheese while mix simmers, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool some.
In tortilla, put some meat mixture; top with grated cheese and roll up.
Don't fold in ends.
Wrap in waxed paper, then in tinfoil, then freeze.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat sugar, flour and eggs with a spoon.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Stir bread cubes in melted margarine.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Can be used as a side dish or dessert.
Excellent with ham!

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, cornmeal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Combine eggs, butter and milk; beat until blended.
Add to dry ingredients and mix just to blend.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into an oiled 8-inch square baking dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Blend graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 pound butter, eggs and vanilla; beat for 5 minutes.
Spread mixture over pressed crumbs and chill.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and place cherries on top.
Chill until served.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, oil and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix alternately.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: mixed vegetables with cheese
directions: Steam vegetables together until tender.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake until lightly browned.

title: mildred's best cornbread
directions: It depends upon the size of baking pan you use.
Mix equal parts of flour and meal for large pan (2 cups each). Add 2 eggs and 3/4 cup mayonnaise and enough milk to stir batter to the consistency of cake batter.
Pour into a greased baking pan and cook in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
You may substitute Pam to grease pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, drain.
Make sauce:
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add grated Cheddar cheese until it melts in the white sauce (I use my microwave).
Stir sauce into the drained macaroni.
Layer macaroni in baking dish with Longhorn cheese slices.
End up with cheese on top.
Add a little bit of milk over the cheese (small amount).
Cook 45 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add together all ingredients, but Parmesan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Chill.

title: tv snack
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients together.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over dry mixture and stir well.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
(Bake in a large roaster pan.)

title: peanut butter fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix brownie mix (dry), flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast and water in a small bowl and set aside.
Combine in a mixing bowl cottage cheese heated to lukewarm, sugar, butter, instant minced onions, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
Add yeast mixture and combine.
Add 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups flour to form a stiff ball, beating well after each addition.
Knead dough and place in a warm place to rise after covering with a cloth, until doubled in size and light, 50 to 60 minutes.
Punch down dough.
Knead again. Turn into well-greased casserole about 8-inches round and let rise again in warm place 30 to 40 minutes until light.
Bake until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: super rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar, salt and raisins in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix 2 slightly beaten eggs, vanilla and nutmeg in 1 quart casserole.
Stir in rice mixture; mix well.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in loaf pan.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix eggs, water, lemon pudding, oil and cake mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, onion dip, Miracle Whip, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over cut-up cauliflower, onion and cucumber. Serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter dessert
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of milk into peanut butter in large bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Place lettuce in the bottom of a 4-quart glass salad bowl. Layer with cucumber, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, onions, pea pods and chicken. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, curry and ginger. Spread over top of salad. Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley if desired. Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: hoss' hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Serves 8 people.

title: corn fritters
directions: Grate corn and scrape cob.
Add egg yolks to corn, then flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add melted butter and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to the mix.
Fry in hot oil, using a small soup ladle to dip out the batter.
Good!
Serves 8.

title: chicken and beef casserole
directions: Layer dried beef, chicken breasts and uncooked bacon in large casserole dish. Mix sour cream and soup together in a large bowl. Spread sour cream mixture over chicken and bacon. Bake at 250° or 300° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate; add margarine to slightly cooled chocolate. Add miniature marshmallows.
Stir all ingredients together and spoon into one large or two small rolls on wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and enjoy.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cut up (in strips) cabbage, peppers and onion. A very large bowl is needed to hold this, but salad will shrink down to half the size. Sprinkle sugar over this. Boil salt, celery seed, vinegar, oil and mustard. Pour over the cabbage mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick 'n chewy crescent bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unroll crescent dough.
Place rectangles in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour condensed milk evenly over dough.
Sprinkle with dry frosting mix. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Drain onion soup and save ingredients to put in meat.
Put onion soup liquid and both cans of mushroom soup in a pot and bring to boil.
Combine hamburger, eggs, bread and onion soup ingredients and make into balls.
Drop balls into liquid and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti (red sauce optional) or mashed potatoes.

title: quick good leftovers
directions: Cut up leftover beef, pork or chicken in small pieces (need not be much).
Place a small amount of margarine or use Pam in skillet. Place cold cooked rice in a hot skillet with chopped onions. Saute.
When onions are cooked, add meat and beaten eggs.
Scramble all together.
Make a green salad and you have a fast, tasty meal.

title: beef pepper steak
directions: *Make sure you count liquid in skillet as part of liquid to mix gravy.

title: pineapple lime milk cooler
directions: Combine milk, pineapple and sherbet.
Blend in a blender or with a mixer.
Garnish with lime slice, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll around so oleo coats sides of pan.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs.
Next, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Sprinkle coconut on top of butterscotch chips, then nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over other ingredients. Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: january thaw
directions: Slowly dissolve sugar and milk in a pan.
Add butter and let boil until it forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and beat well.
Turn into a buttered pan. Cut into squares when cool.
Delicious!

title: crock-pot short ribs
directions: Dust short ribs with flour.
Place in large skillet.
Brown ribs on both sides in oil.
Place in bottom of crock-pot.
Stir together water and soup mix; spoon over meat.
Cover.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove meat; skim off excess fat.
Thicken with roux; serve as gravy.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring to a boil syrup and sugar.
While hot, add peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in slowly Rice Krispies.
Mix well and spread and press in cake pan or a cookie sheet.
Mix chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and melt.
Spread on top.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add garlic powder; drain. Boil cubed zucchini no longer than 5 minutes. Spray casserole with Pam. Layer hamburger, zucchini and 4 ounces of cheese; repeat. Mix soup and water. Pour over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in cool, melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: homespun salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry-with-orange and pineapple with juice. Pour into mold. Can be served with mayonnaise and Cool Whip mixed.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese and cream on medium heat.
Add sausage to cheese mixture.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar with apples; let stand while sifting the dry ingredients together.

title: billie's pea salad
directions: Drain juice from cans of vegetables.
Combine vegetables.
Add chopped bell pepper, onion, celery and pimentos.
Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over other ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: mary lou's greek cheese cake
directions: Slowly add sugar to cream cheese with electric mixer and add eggs one at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Test middle at 1 hour.
Cool completely.
Place fruit on top and refrigerate overnight before serving.
To remove from pan, take knife and cut all around.
Release sides.
Cut and serve.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Freezes well.

title: peas, peas, peas
directions: Put bacon in a pan with 1 quart of cold water; bring to a boil.
Add remainder of ingredients, except peas.
Cook until water is reduced by half.
Add 1 more quart cold water, peas and salt to taste.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding water as necessary, until tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This method works for all kinds of peas and butter beans.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put the apples in a buttered casserole with the water. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put the flour, sugar and margarine or butter into a bowl.
Mix into crumbs. Sprinkle this on top of the apples and bake until apples are cooked at 350° to 375° for about 1 hour.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's, reserving remaining candies for decoration.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: easy breezy lemon cake
directions: * Ingredients listed on package.

title: winesap apples
directions: Peel Winesap apples; cut in halves.
Wrap in Hungry Jack biscuits.
Lay in 11 1/2-inch pan.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Turn into pie shell. Chill for about 4 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Place over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolve.
Add fruit juices and banana, mixing well. Cool.
Freeze until firm.
To serve:
thaw until slushy, then add ginger ale.
Yields 35 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Place drained pineapple in dish. Pour mixed flour and sugar evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle with cheese, then crumbled crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: paradise pie
directions: Fix your pie crust in pie pan.
Slice up enough green tomatoes to almost fill pan (slice very thin).
Put sugar all over them (sweeten to your own taste).
Put black pepper over this and add butter.
Put in some water, also.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Put pie crust on top and make a few holes in top so the juice will come through.
Put sugar and add some more butter on top.
Cook in oven at about 350° until done.

title: secret chocolate sensation
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans. Mix first 4 ingredients. Pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Frost with the last 4 ingredients. Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk. Beat slowly. Fold in whipped topping. Spread on cake. Store frosted cake in the refrigerator.

title: tomato jelly salad (8)
directions: Cook first 10 ingredients until soft.
Remove from heat. Soften gelatin in water; stir until dissolved.
Add and combine with first mixture, strain, chill and pour into mold(s).
To unmold, dip in hot water.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Cook first four ingredients on medium heat and stir occasionally until the chocolate will make a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
When cooled add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Allow to harden and cut into squares.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix and let set.

title: missouri breakfast casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, line the bottom with the cubed bread. Grate the cheese and place on top of the bread. Cook and cool the sausage.
Dice and put on top of the cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix the soup and 1/2 can milk.
Pour over top (mix in extra mushrooms, if desired).
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.
Turn oven off and let set in oven about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding mix. Beat for 1 minute (mixture will be thick). Add pumpkin and spices; beat 1 minute longer. Pour into pie crust. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with whipped topping and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: shrimp greek style
directions: Cook garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add tomatoes; cook about 1 minute.
Add wine, salt, pepper, basil and oregano; cook over moderate heat for about 10 minutes.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jewel's cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheese, seasonings and sour cream or mayonnaise. Add beef and onion.
Form into ball and chill.

title: womack's house fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Cut margarine into mixture until coarse and lumpy.
Put fruit in an 8-inch square, lightly greased pan.
Top with flour-sugar mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown and crisp. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add Wesson oil and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients; add to eggs and oil.
Add nuts and carrots.
Bake at 325° in three 8 or 9-inch pans (or Bundt pan).

title: ma's texas pecan pie
directions: Prepare
pie
crust.
Preheat
oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well with
wire	whisk.	Mix
in corn syrup, sugar, butter or margarine and
vanilla
extract until blended.
Arrange pecan halves in single layer to cover bottom of pie crust.	Pour egg mixture carefully
over
pecans in crust.
Bake for 1 hour or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: italian beef
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Put in a Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients on top of roast.
Cover; put on low heat on top of stove.
Cook for 3 hours, turning meat periodically.
After 3 hours, remove meat and place on platter.
To the sauce, add 4 sliced green peppers and 3 cups water; simmer 1/2 hour.
Slice meat then for sandwiches and pour sauce over meat.

title: tostada mexican quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Let frozen pastry shell stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Do not prick the shell.
In a small bowl, mix avocados, garlic and lemon juice.
Stir in one chopped tomato, 1 tablespoon green chilies and hot pepper sauce. Cover and refrigerate.
Bake pastry shell 7 minutes.
Remove from oven, set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 375 degrees.
In medium skillet, combine ground beef, onion, remaining chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Cook until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain well.
Layer cheese and then ground beef mixture in pastry shell.

In medium bowl combine eggs, half and half, salt and pepper, beating with fork until well mixed, but not frothy. Pour egg mixture over ground beef and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with lettuce, tomato and avocado mixture.
Place corn chips, additional tomato and avocado for guests to help themselves.
Serves 6.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use a tablespoon per cup of hot water.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop the potatoes into bite size pieces, same with the onion. Put salt, onion and potatoes into your saucepan with just enough cold water to cover them, then turn the stove to medium-high until it begins to bubble quickly.
Turn down the heat and cover the pan and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir; pour milk in.
Keep stirring until smooth and hot.
Bon appetit!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use large and deep clear bowl.
Add ingredients, one at a time as given, each in a separate layer.
Do not toss.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Makes about 10 servings.
To serve, dig deep to get portion of each layer.
Will keep at least 2 days in fridge.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together and spread over ham.
Roll ham up.
Cut off ends. Cut into four rolls.
Refrigerate until use.
You can freeze whole rolls until you need them.
They will be easier to cut when slightly frozen.

title: carob cake
directions: Blend
cashews
with
water
until
smooth.
Add honey, carob and
vanilla.
In separate bowl, place dry ingredients. Add hydrogen
peroxide
to liquid and whiz briefly.
Pour wet into dry ingredients.
Stir only to mix well.
Pour gently and quickly into oiled
and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.
Cool and frost.

title: scramble party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Peanuts may be added or cereal may be added according to personal taste.
Makes 9 quarts.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Mix sour cream and egg until well blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese. Dip each chicken breast into mixture until well coated, then roll in bread crumbs.
Once all the chicken is in the baking dish, you can sprinkle cheese on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Measure juice; add water to equal 2 cups. Prepare pudding according to directions, using juice in place of milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix with fruit and refrigerate until cold.
Stir in sliced bananas before serving.
(Recipe doubles easily; sugar-free pudding works well.)

title: quick pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients on low speed of blender.
Add sour cream in little dabs with a spoon; blend with spoon only.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour in batter and bake 45 minutes.

title: best butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast
and
teaspoon sugar in warm water. Let stand
for
several
minutes.
Combine
oleo
with 1/2 cup sugar. Add shortening mixture to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast
to
milk mixture.
Add flour; mix well.
Knead until dough is
smooth
and
elastic.
Place in
oiled pan and let raise until
doubled
in bulk.
Turn onto
floured board. Knead to smooth.
Divide
dough in two parts.
Roll each piece to 12-inch circle.
Cut
each circle into 16 pie pieces.
Roll each piece from base to center.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 42 rolls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Place on cookie sheet with a tablespoon. Let cook (bake at 350°).
When ready, take out of oven.
Roll in white sugar, then place one unwrapped kiss in middle of cookie. Cookie is still hot or the kiss will not stay in.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in the warm water.
Beat egg in bowl and then add yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Place rest of ingredients, one at a time, in order given.
Warm in microwave until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Scoop out with white taco chips.

title: granola bars
directions: In saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Add oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Press in cake pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store in plastic bag in fridge.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Mix together, spread on cocktail rye bread. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350. Oregano to taste. Can be made in advance and frozen. Thaw when needed.

title: lisa ashworth's parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg, then in mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Heat tomato sauce and spices, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top; bake 5 more minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix ingredients with browned meat and simmer for 20 minutes or cook in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add
eggs,
one
at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift
flour
and salt together. Add
alternately with juice
and	flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 for 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are golden brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Beat all ingredients in a large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Pour into pans.
Bake for about 60 to 65 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together. Shape into 1 inch balls. Brown some chopped onion and meatballs together in a large skillet. Drain off fat. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; set pineapple aside. Pour syrup over meatballs. Bring to a boil. Cover, simmer for 10 minutes. Serve on toothpicks with one chunk of pineapple and one meatball on each toothpick. May be served cold or hot.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Core and slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Put in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with water, stirring to mix.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, bring all ingredients to boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: easy yummy dessert
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Let thicken then fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Spread a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half the pudding mixture.
Spread another layer of graham crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Microwave chocolate frosting until soft and spoon and spread over the top layer of graham crackers.
Chill until firm.
Yummmmm.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Melt as much butter as desired in a frypan set at 320° or medium heat.
Cream the cream cheese in mixer bowl on #4 speed until creamy.
Add eggs; beat 1/2 minute on #8 speed.
Scrape bowl and beaters.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Blend in on #4 speed.
Pour mixture into frypan.
Cook slowly, scraping a few times from bottom and sides with a spoon.
Do not stir constantly. Cook only until set, but still moist.
Serve with bacon, ham or sausage.
Garnish with chopped parsley or chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add soup and cheese, stir until cheese melts.
Add well drained broccoli, mix well.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° till bubbly.
Can be made ahead and frozen or stored in refrigerator.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add chopped onion.
Cook about 1 minute.
In a large pot, put tomato juice, ground beef, onion and beans.
Add chili mix or chili powder to taste.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop enough popcorn (salted) to fill a dishpan or extra large pan.
Combine sugar, syrup, water and butter.
Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Pour over popcorn. Mix well with large spoon.
Butter your hands and mold into balls or use two small plastic bowls the same size to make a mold. Work quickly as the syrup on the popcorn dries fast.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together potatoes, pepper, salt and onions.
Mix together with melted butter.
Cook in a baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef soup
directions: Put potato soup in blender.
Cut meat to bite size.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
In small sauce pan, mix broth and soup. Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken. Combine melted margarine, flour, buttermilk, salt and pepper. Pour over chicken. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. (You can add a can of mixed vegetables if desired.)

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix
together
pumpkin,
oil,
sugar and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients, add to mixture.
Bake at 350°.
Best when measured with small ice cream scoop.

title: butterhorns
directions: Blend flour and oleo with pastry blender.
Make a well in the center and add milk and egg yolk.
Stir until the mixture forms a ball and comes away from the sides of the bowl.
Sprinkle with flour and chill overnight or several hours.

title: pride o' pumpkin cake
directions: *Can also use cooked butternut squash.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer cream cheese on bottom
of
a
9	x
13-inch pan. Spread chili
on	 top.
Sprinkle
green	chilies
over
top. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese to cover.
Microwave for 8 to 9 minutes. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: medium white sauce(makes 1 cup)
directions: Heat in a saucepan over low heat the butter.
Blend flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat, add gradually 1 cup milk.
Cook rapidly, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: garlic oil
directions: Peel cloves from garlic heads.
Put cleaned cloves in quart jar and fill with olive oil.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Use for cooking or any oil substitute.
Keep refrigerated!

title: apricot delight
directions: Put the apricots through a sieve.
Add confectioners sugar. Whip the cream until stiff and fold into apricots.
Add moist coconut.
Chill.
Serve in sherbet glasses.
Top with whipped cream and coconut.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add oil, vanilla, vinegar and water; mix well.
Bake in Pyrex or cake pan (12 x 8 x 2-inches) at 350° for 25 minutes.
Leave in pan and cover with topping.

title: diet frosting
directions: Cook over boiling water.
Beat to stiff peaks, then to spreading consistency.

title: hungarian easter cheese(cirak)
directions: Bring milk to a boil in saucepan.
Beat eggs slightly; add gradually to boiled milk.
Cook over low heat for about 7 minutes, or until it starts to thicken and forms curds.
Add seasonings and sugar, stirring constantly so mixture will not scorch.
Pour mixture into a cloth or cheesecloth bag; squeeze and tie opening tightly.
Let drain about 2 hours, or until set.
Refrigerate. Slice before serving.

title: apricot salad 1994
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Stir in jello and let cool.
Stir in buttermilk.
Put in Cool Whip and pecans.
Put in a mold or dish and let set.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix pineapple, orange pieces and cottage cheese thoroughly. Add powdered Jell-O and stir until completely mixed.
Stir in whipped topping.
When these ingredients are completely mixed, stir in the nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate salad.
Sets in 30 minutes.
Better left overnight before using.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: Pound veal until 1/4-inch thick.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each piece of veal.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end, secure rolls with wooden picks.

title: fried pies
directions: In a saucepan over high heat, cover the dried fruit with 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Cook until the fruit begins to get tender and the liquid is reduced by 1/2 cup.
Add 1/2 cup of water and 1 cup of sugar and boil until fruit is soft, thick and mushy. Do not let the fruit burn.	Stir occasionally.
Set aside to cool. In a large bowl, combine flour, salt and soda.
Cut in 1/2 cup of lard.
Add enough buttermilk to make a dough.
On a floured board, roll the pastry out thinly.
Cut in 5-inch rounds and place a spoonful of filling in the center of each round.
Moisten the edges and fold over and seal with fork tines.
In an iron skillet, melt lard 1/2-inch deep.
Gently place pastries in the hot fat and fry until brown on one side.
Do not overcrowd.
Turn and brown on the other side.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Eat hot or cold.
Yield:
8 pies.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Stir after 20 minutes.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Put in greased 8-inch pan. Top with fruit.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
More sugar may be needed if fruit is tart.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter and oil until onions are tender; drain meat mixture.
Add garlic, salt, chili powder, tomatoes, corn and olives.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Combine egg and milk; add to corn meal slowly.
Add to meat mixture a little at a time, stirring well.
Pour into a greased casserole in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese and melt the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shaker bottle and refrigerate.

title: cornbread and tomato salad
directions: Mix Jiffy cornbread mix as directed on box.
Bake until light brown; cool.
Crumble 1/2 cornbread in bowl.
Add 1/2 of tomatoes, then 1/2 of onions and repeat cornbread, tomatoes and onion.

title: creamed sweet corn
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and simmer uncovered
for 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through.
Yields:
4 servings.

title: yoghurt cake
directions: Beat eggs, yoghurt, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Add baking powder, lemon rind and sugar.
Mix well for 5 minutes.
Add flour to the mixture.
Pour batter in a well-greased cake pan; bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a well preheated oven.
Cool for 15 minutes before you unmold.
Sprinkle powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pumpkin silk pie
directions: In large mixing bowl combine cream cheese, pumpkin, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread filling into crust.
Top with pecans, if desired.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: caputo's italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water and squeeze out moisture.
Break into pieces and add to crumbled beef and pork.
Add egg, milk, spices and Romano cheese.
Mix well by hand.
Shape into 2-inch balls and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake in oven at 375° for 25 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with spaghetti sauce and pasta. Makes 10 to 12 meatballs.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Sprinkle meat generously with tenderizer, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Spread generously over meat all other ingredients, except barbecue sauce. Wrap meat tightly in foil.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Uncover or loosen foil.
Bake 5 to 6 hours more at 200° or until tender.
(For smaller brisket, bake 1 hour at 300°, then uncover and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 200°.)
Cool.
Slice to serve.
Spread each slice with barbecue sauce.
Cover baking pan with foil.
Return to oven and bake another hour at 200° before serving to 12 persons. Leftover meat may be frozen.
The brisket makes good sandwiches.

title: wicket's wedgies
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on English muffins. Broil until melted. Eat whole for breakfast or quarter for appetizers.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix batter, test pancake.
Add more flour if necessary.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Combine diced chicken, dry stuffing mix, undiluted soup, melted margarine, chicken broth, celery, onion, milk and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter jelly roll size baking pan.
Set aside.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix together and place in miniature muffin pans. Do not grease pans. Bake at 425° until brown on top.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until served.
Bon Appetit!

title: crock-pot barbecue sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 3 hours, then on high for 5 hours.
Stir with wire whisk until meat is shredded.
Serve on buns.
Serves 12.

title: lima-tuna bake(mama's recipe)
directions: Combine lima beans, tuna, celery soup and water.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cut cheese in triangles and place on top of toast triangles and arrange along center of casserole.
Bake at 350° until beans are tender (25 to 35 minutes).

title: upside-down pizza(low-fat)
directions: In a skillet saute turkey, celery, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with your choice of vegetable options.
Pour the tomato sauce over this and top with cheese.
Cover with the crescent rolls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.
Set for 5 minutes before slicing.
Yields 8 servings.

title: "local kine" fish
directions: Scale and clean fish.
Cut fish lengthwise as close to the bone as you can.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish (not too much). Place ti leaves in foil covered baking pan and place fish on ti leaves.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Then put in crock-pot with all other ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lynn's three bean bake
directions: Cook bacon crisp.
Saute ground beef and onion together.
Place in crock-pot, beans, catsup and brown sugar.
Add beef and bacon to crock-pot.
Cook in crock-pot 5 hours on low setting.

title: chicken in foil(portions are for 1 serving)
directions: On a 12-inch square of heavy-duty foil, place chicken in center.
Top with vegetables, pepper, tarragon and lemon juice. Wrap tight, place on baking sheet.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix milk and oil together; do not stir.
Mix with flour. Knead 10 times; roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa and boil for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: scalloped corn and broccoli
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, flour and cheese.
Fold in partially thawed broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 5 or 6 people.

title: simply fudge(sugarless)
directions: Heat milk over low heat.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk and stir until dissolved.
Add butter flavoring and sugar substitute. Blend well.
Remove from heat and add extracts and food coloring. Pour into small pan.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serves 1.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix topping and pour over cake mix.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add to mixture the milk and Cheddar cheese.
Add in remaining ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie(not so sweet)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and butter until creamy, add the corn syrup and pecans, stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet & sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic, salt, and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes covered.
Start on high, then simmer. Put all beans in a bowl.
Add cooked mixture.
Add bacon. Mix. Pour into 3 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° 1 hour and 15 minutes covered or place in crock pot.

title: marshmallow cream fudge from nestle
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into waxed lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm (about 2 hours).

title: sauerbraten klopse(sauerbraten meatballs)
directions: Mix beef, milk, crumbs, cloves, allspice, salt and pepper. Form into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in hot oil. Drain off fat. Add 1 cup of water, vinegar, ginger, bay leaf and brown sugar. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Skim off fat.
Remove meatballs and keep them warm.
Mix flour and 2 tablespoons of water.
Slowly stir into the pan juices to make gravy.
Pour gravy over meatballs.
Serve with buttered noodles.
Serves 4.

title: fried johnnycakes(virgin island native recipe)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add water; make stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut in rounds; prick with fork; fry in hot deep fat.
Serve hot.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Measure Master Cake Mix, chocolate and 3/4 cup buttermilk into bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat 2 more minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans which have been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix the cake mix as directed.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan well.
Spread the coconut and pecans in bottom of cake pan.
Pour cake mixture over this.
Blend the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop in spoonfuls onto cake mix.
(Be sure to cover mixture with cake mix.)
Bake at 325° until done.

title: beef and veggie stir-fry
directions: In skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil to 375 degrees.
Add the onion and green pepper. Saute just until tender, stirring constantly.
Remove to a plate, using a slotted spoon. Add 2 more tablespoons oil and the celery, zucchini, yellow squash and carrots.
Cook just until crisp tender.
Remove to plate with slotted spoon.
Add the remaining 2 tablespoons oil to the skillet.
Saute the steak just until it begins to change color. Add the vegetables back to the skillet.
Add the soy sauce and stir.
Serve immediately over the rice.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Place all ingredients in pan in layers (pie filling, pineapple and cake mix). Press all ingredients down, then sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Melt the 2 sticks oleo and pour over entire cake. Bake in oven at 325° to 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: oahu appetizer
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, ham and mustard.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and chives.
If necessary, chill for ease in handling.
(Makes about 2 cups cheese mixture.)

title: raisin bar cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water. Remove from stove; add soda and Crisco. Stir. Add all dry ingredients. Mix well. Pour into prepared jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour a thin mixture of powdered sugar and milk over cookies when you take from oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased 3 quart casserole dish. Cover top with:
1 cup crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup oleo mixed together.
Bake on 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: In large bowl, add first 3 ingredients and blend on low speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
To the remaining mixture, add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon evenly over base in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: larrupin potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle with extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade butter roll
directions: Roll out dough until thin.
Cut into squares.
Cut butter into small chunks, placing them on the dough.
Sprinkle nutmeg and teaspoon sugar over each roll, then fold the dough, closing it up. Then pour milk over them.
Bake at 400°, making about 12.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, eggs and soup.
Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Layer again.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: beef tagaliah
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix in medium bowl the sour cream, cream cheese and onion; set aside.
Place 2 cooked, drained noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture and 1/2 of meat sauce.
Lay 2 more noodles on meat sauce; layer again with cream cheese mixture, then meat sauce.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory ranch potatoes
directions: Combine warm mashed potatoes with remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.

title: my favorite pie crust(for 1 pie, top and bottom)
directions: Cut in first 3 ingredients with pastry whip just until changes to yellowish color.
Mix in water with fork, lifting up from bottom.
Pick up and form in 2 balls, without working dough too much.

title: baked stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove pulp, leaving 1/2-inch of outer shell.
Dice pulp.
Saute onions, mushrooms, seasonings and meat in margarine.
Stir in tomato paste, wheat germ and eggplant pulp.
Cook until meat is slightly done.
Spoon meat mixture into eggplant shell and place in an oiled ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley. Yields 6 servings, approximately 270 calories per serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cube.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed. Add chicken to this mixture.
Layer Ritz crackers over chicken. Pour butter over crackers.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook juice, cornstarch and spices until thick; add salt and stir.
Add sliced apples and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and top with second shell.
Prick top shell and place some magarine on top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: friendship tea
directions: Use 1 1/2 teaspoons mix per cup of boiling water.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain and rinse well under cold water.
Combine the next 8 ingredients in a screw-top jar and shake well to blend.
Toss linguine, mushrooms, scallions and cheese with first mixture and chill.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange tuna on top.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper.
Mix milk and soup and pour over all.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and dice.
Pour sugar over them and set aside. Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice and vanilla to sugar and apples.
Then add all dry ingredients.
Pour into a tube pan, Bundt pan or heavy large skillet.	Sprinkle chips over top and bake.	Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.	Sometimes I don't even peel the apples.

title: apple or rhubarb crunch
directions: Place fruit in a baking dish.
Mix flour and cinnamon together and sprinkle over fruit.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and butter and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake until topping is crunchy and brown and fruit is done.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: elweno's cookies
directions: Mix sugar, lard, egg and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Press out in 12 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° until light brown (not long).

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased pan.
Combine oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut into butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions; cook for 2 minutes.
Add flour; mix well.
Add milk; bring to a boil.
Add crab; stir constantly, bringing to a boil.
Simmer on very low heat.
Serves 4 small servings.

title: german chocolate surprize cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and bake cake as directed on package.
Punch holes in top of cake with a large fork.
Combine chocolate syrup and milk.
Pour over the cake, allowing it to soak into holes.
Cover and allow cake to cool in refrigerator overnight (or 4 hours).
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: snack bits
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients in large baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together in saucepan.
Heat this mixture and mix well.
Pour over first mixture, making sure it is well covered. Place in 200° oven.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes with wooden spoon.
Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: rolled chicken breast
directions: Flatten each breast half with meat mallet or edge of heavy saucer.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Divide stuffing into six portions and place on chicken breast.
Roll each chicken breast into a roll and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a casserole dish and cover with soup mixed with one can of water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Toss dry ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to the dry ingredients.
Spread on baking sheets and bake in 250° oven about 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite size pieces.
(This should take about 2 months.)
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Simmer over kerosene stove at 465° for about 4 weeks.
Serves approximately 3,800 people, but if more are expected, add the two rabbits.
This should only be done if absolutely necessary, because most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and pudding mix in large mixing bowl. Beat until creamy and smooth.
Beat in flour and soda, then stir in oats, fruit mix and raisins.
Nuts if desired.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: m&m's jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour and soda together and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts. Drop teaspoon of mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes depending on size of cookie or until lightly browned. Cool on cookie sheet 2 to 3 minutes before removing to wire rack. Yields approximately 32 cookies.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the fat with the sugar.
Add the beaten egg; then add milk alternately with the sifted flour and other ingredients. Lastly add the floured nuts.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch dollar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt together the butter and shortening.
Add sugars and beat well.
Add eggs until batter has light color.
Stir in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Season chicken and brown in oil; remove chicken.
Brown sausage, then remove from oil.
Cook seasonings until tender. When brown, add water, then add chicken and sausage.
Cook chicken until tender.
Add rice and cook uncovered over medium heat until all water is absorbed.
Cover and steam until rice is cooked; stir occasionally.
If jambalaya is too dry, add a little water.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dinner day before
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish (Creamettes are raw). Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts.
Toss with 2 tablespoons butter and salt.
Combine sugar, 1/2 cup butter and corn syrup in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until mixture turns light caramel color.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over corn mixture; stir to coat evenly.
Spread out on cookie sheet or waxed paper.
When cool, break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: corn fritters(pancake style)
directions: In 1676, fifty homes and warehouses were destroyed by fire. Clearly, something better was needed than the Jynk's "engines" and it was voted to buy the very best London had to offer.
America's first practical fire engine, a device for pumping water, operated manually and was put into service on January 27, 1678.
It consisted of a wooden box, about three feet long, eighteen inches wide, standing on four legs with protruding front and rear handles that enabled it to be carried to the fire.
Mounted inside was a pump that fed a flexible, snake-like nozzle.
Water was supplied to the box by the bucket brigade.
Thomas Atkins, Captain of this rig, was appointed America's first paid firefighting officer.
He appointed twelve assistants and together they formed our first paid fire department in America.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 egg. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Cream remaining ingredients and pour over crust. Bake at 350° until light brown or approximately 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger, chili powder and sugar.
Drain off grease. In large bowl combine all ingredients except dressing and Doritos. Just before serving, mix in dressing, pour in chips and serve.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a large baking dish.
Pour Italian dressing over top.
Marinate in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Remove chops and keep marinade.

title: baked beans and ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat; add onion, green pepper and beans.
Simmer 10 minutes; add tomato paste, catsup, water, salt, pepper and molasses.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In large saucepan, mix jello mix, sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to rolling boil.
Will change from cloudy to clear color.
Set in refrigerator.
Slice strawberries, then add to jello mixture.
Pour in pie shell.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour to set up.

title: vanilla wafer cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Chill.
Roll thin.
Cut with cutter dipped in flour.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: easy oven fried coating mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep refrigerated.
Use mixture to coat beef, pork and poultry.
Using 1 to 2 cups of mixture at a time, coat meat pieces and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
A great recipe to keep on hand.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until coarse.
Beat eggs well and add to sweet milk. Add currants to coarse mixture together with milk mixture.
Mix well and put out on floured baking sheet.
Roll out to 1 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shape.
Place on greased cookie sheet; dot each biscuit with generous piece of butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: aunt lavon's jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water and add 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Drain pineapple and add to Jell-O.
Chill.
When Jell-O is set, slice the bananas on top.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: You may use any vegetables.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Cook with lid on in iron skillet.

title: esther's minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a large kettle.
Add onion, celery and parsley. Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, soup mix, bouillon cubes, water, cabbage, vegetables, macaroni and spices.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Add undrained kidney beans.
Cover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: egg and sausage casserole(family favorite on christmas morning)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown sausage. Drain and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine milk, eggs, dry mustard and salt.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in cheese, bread cubes and sausage.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apple slices in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Combine remaining 3/4 cup sugar and flour in a small saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup butter and water.
Place over medium heat until syrup boils, stirring constantly.
Pour half of the syrup over apples.
Prepare pastry and place over apples. Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Pour remaining half of syrup over top of pastry and bake 20 more minutes or until pastry is golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole.

title: chip dip rodeo
directions: Sieve pork and beans; add shredded cheese, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, garlic salt, onion salt and cayenne.
Mix well.
Heat.
Serve with potato chips or corn chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: flan
directions: This recipe uses a 2 1/2 x 9-inch aluminum ring mold.

title: bean and beet salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Cover vegetables with liquid.
Mix and refrigerate at least 2 days, stirring very gently once each day.
Keeps very well.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add bay leaf, tomatoes, brown sugar, basil, salt and pepper; cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Baste with liquid every 20 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with parsley.

title: crustless bacon and egg quiche
directions: Fry or microwave bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside. If you use sausage, fry until done.
Combine milk, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and pepper; beat 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon (sausage) and cheese on top of egg mixture; gently press below surface with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: darlene's hot rolls
directions: Cook 2 to 3 potatoes in plenty of water; keep warm.
Mix together 2 cups lukewarm potato water, the sugar and salt.
Mix in the dry yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Add the eggs and Crisco.
Mix in, using a spoon or mixer the mashed potatoes and 3 cups flour. Mix with spoon or hands, adding 4 1/2 to 5 cups of flour.
Put in large container; let rise once.
Punch down good before putting into large container, covered; place in refrigerator.
When ready to use, shape or cut out and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° until very brown, about 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine dry onion soup and 1/2 cup of water. Beat in eggs. Add hamburger. Shape meat into 40 balls and brown. Combine sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce, 3/4 cup water and brown sugar. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 9 x 13 pan. Add meatballs and pour remaining mixture over meat. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix
together and keep in tight container in refrigerator until
needed.
Pat
into roll shape or roll out on waxed paper and cut in circles.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Can be stored about 5 days.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar. Add well beaten eggs, margarine, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 cup coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle remaining coconut over pie.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: microwave tuna and noodles
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes on High.
Stir twice.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes.
May be sprinkled with 1 can (1 3/4 ounce) shoestring potatoes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok; add scallions, celery and meat. Stir until vegetables are barely tender.
Add rice and sprouts. Heat quickly while stirring.
Beat egg with soy sauce and ginger. Add rice to mixture; cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add whole and creamed corn and cornbread mix.
Stir with fork.
Add garlic, onion, sugar and eggs.
Fold sour cream in gently.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: frozen yogurt
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or muffin cups.
Cover and place in freezer.
Freeze at least 4 hours. Unmold and serve.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Beat eggs. Mash bananas.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: onion soup
directions: In a large pot melt butter with oil.
Stir in onions and salt. Cook uncovered over low
heat 20 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle onions with flour. Stir
and
cook
3 minutes.
Remove from heat. In separate pan,
bring beef stock to simmer.
Pour hot stock into onions.
Return
soup
to
low
heat and simmer, partially covered for 40 minutes.
Skim
off
fat.
To
serve, place croutons in individual soup bowls.
Ladle soup over them. Sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine cheeses, parsley, salt, pepper, eggs and bread crumbs for filling.
Spoon into manicotti.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange manicotti in a single layer over sauce.
Brown Italian sausage; drain.
Cover manicotti with sausage.
Cover sausage with remaining sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 15 minutes longer.
