title: bread pudding(first choice)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine bread, milk and cream.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onions in margarine 5 minutes, high heat. Reduce the heat to medium and stir in the flour.
Add the broth (or water), garlic powder and pepper.
Bring back to a boil.
Add broccoli (defrosted) and simmer 10 minutes.
Add the milk, half & half and cheese and cook until the cheese melts.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli 3 to 4 minutes. Cook and drain rice. Set aside. In pan, saute onions, butter and celery. Add celery soup, milk and cheese and melt thoroughly. Combine rice and broccoli; cook for few minutes, stirring. Place ingredients in casserole dish and sprinkle top with crumbs. Cook for 30 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: mock cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until very thick.
Let cool.
Mix Crisco, butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Add flour mixture and continue mixing until creamy.

title: carrot-pepper relish
directions: Cook carrots in 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) until crisp-tender, 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add green peppers and onions.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables; stir. Cover and refrigerate no longer than 3 weeks.
Makes 10 cups relish.

title: mom's fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until creamy.
Add the eggs and beat 10 minutes.
Be sure to time and beat 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in nuts, cherries and coconut.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open the oven door for 1 hour.

title: raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans.
In large bowl, beat at low speed all ingredients except apples, raisins and nuts for 2 minutes.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: janice miller's christmas cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and milk. Mix together 3 cups flour, the soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Add alternating with flour to batter the rum, then add fruit and pecans.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: danish breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into small pieces and put in bottom of an oiled 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover the bread with the cooked sausage, then the cheese.
Mix eggs, 1 1/4 cups milk and salt; heat well. Pour over the cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup milk with the mushroom soup; pour over casserole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crunchy sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork.
Add water.
Simmer covered for 1 hour or until tender.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, juice and soy sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour over pork.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (hash browns, onion and mayo).
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with crackers or potato chips and serve.

title: german venison goulash
directions: Brown cubes of meat in bacon fat.
Add onion and other ingredients.
Simmer slowly over low heat or in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: steak supper(in foil)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Tear off a 2 1/2-foot length of 18-inch wide foil.
Place meat in center; sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with vegetables.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Fold foil over and seal to keep juices in.
Place on baking sheet. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Drain well and put on paper towel 1/2 cup of each of the following:
pimento, dill pickles, green beans all chopped, English peas, whole corn, optional.
Crisp bacon or ham to suit families' taste.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix in a bowl the vegetables, mayonnaise, onion and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Put into a greased baking dish.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Top with crushed Ritz (that have been mixed with 1 stick melted margarine).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Wash zucchini.
Cut lengthwise; scrape insides out.
Put scraped zucchini in a bowl; add all other ingredients except tomatoes.
Mix well and stuff zucchini.
Place in baking pan which has been oiled or sprayed with vegetable spray. Pour tomatoes over zucchini.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour.

title: christmas nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, chopped fruits, broken nuts and lemon extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Can be baked in 3 small loaf pans or 1 large tube pan.
Add small pan of water in oven while baking to keep from drying.
Refrigerate for better cutting.
Pans can be lined with foil.

title: versatile chicken
directions: In a 1 cup measure, combine buttermilk, bouillon and oregano. Let stand 10 minutes.
Place chicken in a large bowl.
Pour mixture over chicken; toss to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes.
In paper or plastic bag, combine flour and paprika.
Shake each piece of chicken in bag to coat.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: drunk wienies
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Mix and add all other sauce ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Pour over 2 pounds of weenies.
Heat in 350° oven for 20 minutes or cut wienies into bite size pieces, heat in chafing dish and serve with picks on the side for hors d'oeuvres.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix well with a spoon; do not use mixer.
Do not grease pan. Pour batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable kugel *(good for passover)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into margarine-greased 2-quart ovenproof dish, ring mold or muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry grilled chicken salad
directions: Arrange on serving platter as listed.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake according to directions using an oblong pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Remove cake from oven when done.
While still warm, punch holes in cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour cream of coconut over top of cake.
Then pour sweetened condensed milk over top of cake. Refrigerate for several hours.
Remove from refrigerator and cover top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place lettuce in serving bowl.
Top with onion, then celery and then green pepper.
Cover vegetable layers with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and then bacon.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Makes about 8 salad servings or 4 entree servings.

title: b.l.t. salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon. Mix thoroughly.
Chill. Add bacon before serving.
Mix lightly.
Serve.

title: hot broccoli cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in crock-pot or microwave.
Serve with chips (recipe may be halved).

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Bring juices to a boil.
Add jello.
Remove from heat.
Add Coke and chill until partly congealed.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts to cooled jello.
Mold in a jello salad.
When you unmold jello, garnish with whipped cream and Bing cherries.

title: no bake lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks well.
Add milk and beat well.
Add lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Pour into baked crust.
Beat egg whites until partly stiff; add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Finish beating until stiff and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place in 350° oven just long enough for meringue to brown.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix in a large bowl banana pudding mix, sour cream, Cool Whip and milk.
Mix until pudding thickens.
Add your bananas, also your cookies.
Leave some to put on top.
Ready to eat when finished.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in cup of sour cream until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, beans and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 can onion rings.
Mix gently.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove and debone.
Cook noodles in broth.
Add vegetables and chopped eggs. Place in casserole dish. Cover with cheese slices and bake until cheese is melted.

title: rocky bars
directions: In double boiler, melt chips, milk and margarine.
Combine with marshmallows and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan lined with wax paper.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In soup pot, brown meat; drain.
Cook noodles in separate pot and drain.
While noodles are cooking, add all other ingredients to beef; cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add noodles to soup mixture and heat through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top of each bowl.

title: creamy red potato salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 10 side dish servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake per box instructions.
Crumble cake into bottom of large glass bowl (punch bowl will work), then layer mousse, Cool Whip and crumbled candy bars.
Repeat layers and chill.

title: batter rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Pour or drop into greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be stored for 2 to 3 days in refrigerator before baking.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 package of taco cheese.
Chill overnight.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, olives, etc. (taco toppings of your choice). End with package of taco cheese.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add remaining ingredients and mix. Spread and roll flour tortillas; slice.

title: jamaican banana pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk to obtain the desired consistency.
Bake on hot griddle until light brown.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas, which have been dipped in hot stock just long enough to soften, in shallow 3-quart buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt.
Add in order:
chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Stir the first mixture into the second mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes in 2 loaf pans.

title: easy salad
directions: Fold dry jello into cottage cheese.
Drain and fold in mandarin oranges, pineapple and small carton of Cool Whip.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage
and
drain.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender
on	low
heat.
Set
aside.
In
large pot, cook water, rice and
soup mix.
Bring to boil for 7 minutes.
In a large casserole dish, mix everything together.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef fricassee
directions: Cook celery, green pepper and onion in melted margarine over low heat until tender, but not brown.
Add beef and cook until all pink color is gone. Stir beef as it cooks.

Add flour and mix. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add to beef. Stir until well blended. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Turn to low heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked rice or mashed potatoes.

title: vienna tarts
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until well blended and fluffy. Add flour; knead to a smooth dough.
Cover; chill several hours. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick into rectangles.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

Place 1/4 teaspoon jelly on each square at the corner. Beginning at the corner, fold edge over, completely covering jelly. Press down to seal and roll square diagonally into crescent shape. Brush with egg yolk mixed with milk.
Sprinkle with nuts or dip into nut bowl.
Place on greased baking sheets; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on cake racks.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake pizza dough according to directions.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix together the Hellmann's mayonnaise, cream cheese and dry Ranch salad dressing.
Spread on the cooled crust.
Top with your choice of cut up veggies.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Pat down cheese and chill. Cut into serving pieces. Serve cold.

title: orange junk
directions: Crust:
Mix vanilla wafers, margarine and ground pecans well. Spread in a Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Arrange broccoli in a shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Pour soup over top and sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups All-Bran and set aside.
Cream the shortening and
sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and scalded bran. Sift flour, soda and salt and add 4 cups All-Bran to liquid mixture. Beat until blended. Add raisins. This can be stored in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Muffins can be baked at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Put in casserole and cover with strips of cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 minutes.

title: double cheese meat roll
directions: Combine the ground beef, eggs, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce with cheese, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12-inches, on waxed paper. Sprinkle shredded cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in shallow baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain excess fat.
Pour remaining sauce with cheese over roll and bake an additional 15 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pennsylvania dutch style green beans
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain and crumble, reserving 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Saute onion lightly in bacon drippings.
Stir in cornstarch, dry mustard, salt and reserved bean liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in brown sugar, vinegar and beans.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon into serving dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate peanut butter sauce for ice cream
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips melt and mixture is smooth. Refrigerate leftover sauce.
Reheat before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bread with dip
directions: Cut out top of bread and pull out pieces of bread until you have a thick shell of bread remaining.
Mix all other ingredients together and place inside bread shell.
Replace top and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with bread pieces around loaf.
You may also use crackers if you wish.
Great!!

title: red velvet cake(three layers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into three 9-inch pans.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges 5 minutes in salted water; drain; pat dry.
Spread potatoes in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; chill until slightly thick. Cream together cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add gelatin and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo together.
Put 2/3 on bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add the filling; sprinkle with rest of graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares and serve plain or garnish with fruit.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add beans and Ro-Tel.
Cut Velveeta cheese into chunks and melt on low heat until melted and mixed well.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: calumet one egg cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder and salt, sift 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly, add sugar gradually, creaming together until blended and light.
Add egg and beat very thoroughly.
Add flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla; put in a 8 x 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving at least 1 1/2 cups syrup.
Combine marmalade, margarine, spices and syrup.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Reduce heat; gently stir in fruit.
Heat 20 minutes.
Serve warm with meat dishes.
Serves 8.

title: salmon wiggle
directions: Drain liquid from canned salmon into measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Remove skin from salmon; set aside.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables together and mix in remainder of ingredients. Cook on low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Put in clean, hot, 1/2 pint jars. Seal.
Hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese, Ranch dressing and horseradish.
Spread on top of crescent rolls.
Top with cauliflower, broccoli, green peppers, onions, tomatoes and cheese (grated).

title: jello carrot mold
directions: Combine water and Jell-O.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well. Put into 1 1/2-pint ring mold which has been rinsed in cold water. Chill until jelled.

title: kari's cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla, lemon juice, eggs and sugar.
When well mixed, pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is lightly brown.
Put in fridge overnight; top with one of the fruits.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into a log.
Can sprinkle with paprika.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Dip in strawberries; eat!

title: coconut cheesecake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until blended well.
Fold into largest graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center sets.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight. Prior to serving: Spread Cool Whip on top.
Toast angel flake coconut and sprinkle on top.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add eggs, oil and milk.
Store in covered container and use as needed.
Use baking paper cups in muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast surprise
directions: Layer the first 3 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard together and pour over layered ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Add soup and milk.
Pour over entire mixture in the morning and bake at 300° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into an oblong greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Cream Crisco and butter or margarine.
Add gradually sugar and eggs to the Crisco and butter.
(Beat after each egg.)
Add milk mixture. Alternate with dry ingredients.
Bake at 330° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in undrained pineapple and strawberries.
Stir until strawberries thaw.
Chill until gelatin thickens.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into 6 1/2 to 7-cup ring mold.
Chill briefly until layer is gently set (do not refrigerate remaining gelatin).
Spoon sour cream evenly over gelatin in mold.
Carefully spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream layer.
Chill until firm.
(Great for Christmas Dessert.)

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well coated.
Pour into greased baking dish (12-inch or 10 x 6-inch oblong dish).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: crawfish extraordinaire
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until blended.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and green onion; cook until clear.
Add crawfish and cook over low fire about 10 minutes.
Add white wine and simmer until blended.
Slowly add cream and simmer over low fire. Do not boil or it will curdle.
Add seasonings to taste.
Serve over cooked noodles or toast points.

title: mexican bean dip(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam.
Spread beans in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle half of cheese over beans.
Pour salsa over cheese, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and top with sour cream.

title: jello punch
directions: Fix jello according to box directions and let cool.
Dissolve sugar in 2 cups boiling water; let cool.
Beat jello mixture and then add sugar water.
Mix thoroughly.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 25.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth. Pour ingredients into two 9-inch greased pie pans.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes its own crust.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Mix until thick, about 2 minutes.
Chill until set, about 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream or topping.
Spread pudding mix on half the crackers and top with remaining crackers.
Wrap sandwiches individually in plastic wrap and freeze until firm.
Use leftover pudding for dessert another day.
Makes 16 sandwiches.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds. Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.

title: strawberry tunnel cream cake
directions: Slice cake 1 inch from top, crosswise.
Cut tunnel in bottom half of cake.
Save cake pieces you cut out of cake.
Mix softened cream cheese with mixer.
Add milk, lemon juice and almond extract to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in strawberries and cake pieces.
Put mixture into tunnel of cake.
Put top back on; ice with Cool Whip.
Decorate with whole strawberries.
Serves 12.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup oil and 1 egg.
Mixture will be crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for later.
Put crumbly mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together the cream cheese, lemon juice, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Pour over top of baked crust.
Sprinkle reserved cake mix over top; bake for 15 minutes more at 350° or until top is browned.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into a prepared pastry shell.
Bake 40 minutes. Cool, then chill.
Top with whipped cream or topping.
Garnish as you wish.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order.
Serve with taco chips.
A very good dip.

title: pepperoni broccoli pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter in pan and add pepperoni.
When butter is melted and pepperoni makes a sauce, add broccoli.
Toss together to coat broccoli.
Add pepperoni/broccoli mixture to cooked pasta.
Toss in Parmesan cheese.
Add garlic powder to taste.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a buttered 8 x 12 (2-quart) flat casserole dish.

Mix soup and sour cream; heat and pour over chicken. Mix poppy seed and crackers and place on top of chicken. Melt margarine or butter and pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly. DO NOT FREEZE.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in roaster or Dutch oven with tight fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: chicken pineapple cheese supreme
directions: Cook broccoli; pound chicken with mallet until 1/4-inch thick. Combine flour, salt and pepper and coat chicken with mixture. Saute in melted margarine, turning once until no longer pink. Place a pineapple ring on each chicken piece, top with a broccoli spear and a cheese slice.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and stir with a large wooden spoon, about 30 strokes.
Grease and flour pans. Make 4 thin layers.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and Cool Whip together.
Pour into crust. Chill until set and keep chilled.

title: guacamole
directions: Place all ingredients except 2 to 3 pieces avocado in a blender.
Process until smooth.
Remove cover and add remaining pieces of avocado.
Process with 2 fast pulses to chop avocado. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Fix
ice cream so it can be cut into
slices.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, shortening, butter
and vanilla.
Add 1/2
of dry cake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Stir
in
remaining dry cake mix.
Divide
this
dough
into
4 equal parts.
Roll each part approximately 6 x 10-inches.
(Flour table and dough to roll.) Cut approximately 3 x 2 1/2-inches.
Place these on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick
with
fork.
Bake
6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool and form into sandwiches.
Yields 16 sandwiches.
Nicer if
left in freezer 24 hours before eating, but who can wait?

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add 7-Up.
Bake in 3 layer lightly greased pans (no flour), at 300°.

title: tuna cheese log
directions: Mix all together; roll up and chill overnight.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet, brown strips of steak with onions.
Stir in mix and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Add 3 tablespoons soy sauce; stir until thickened.
Cover and simmer.
Add 2 large bell peppers cut into thin strips.
Add 2 tomatoes cut into wedges.
Simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: cappuccino fudge cake
directions: Spread almonds	in single layer on baking sheet.
Place in cold oven;	bake
at
350°	for
9	to 11 minutes, stirring occasionally until golden brown.
Cool;
leave
oven
at 350°. Cream shortening with sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond extracts until fluffy.
Combine flour
with	cocoa powder, coffee crystals, baking soda, baking
powder
and salt;
mix well.
Blend dry ingredients into
creamed
mixture	alternately with milk. Stir in	1/2 cup
toasted
almonds.
Pour
into	greased
and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking
pan.	Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until pick inserted in center	comes
out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with Cappuccino
Fudge
Icing
and	sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup toasted almonds.
Makes 16 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat and one onion in 1 quart of water and simmer until meat loosens from bones.
Cut into pieces.
Discard bones.
Add salt, peppers and vegetables.
Stir often while mixture comes to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 3 to 5 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
This makes approximately 6 quarts of stew.
This can be frozen.

title: spinach roll
directions: Spread dough on lightly greased baking pan.
Saute onion in olive oil until golden brown.
Add chopped spinach and saute together until thoroughly mixed.
Spread on top of dough.
Roll tightly into a jelly roll shape.
Bake at 350°
until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: quick sausage casserole(creole)
directions: Blend together soup and water; add rice, green pepper, sausage and onion.
Bake in a greased 1-quart casserole in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat oil and brown the meat.
Saute onion and garlic.
Drain.
If you use Italian sausage boil it for 20 minutes.
In a 12-quart stock pan over medium heat, transfer the meat, onions and garlic and add the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, herbs and water.
Add the sausage and/or the chicken at this time also.
Bring it to a boil, turn down to simmer.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti, tortellini or any other pasta or rice.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lay ham and cheese on top of chicken breast, roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Dip in melted butter and roll in bread crumbs.
Bake until done, about 45 minutes, in a 350° oven. Remove toothpick before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in pan.
Mix Dream Whip as package says.
Add cream cheese at room temperature to Dream Whip. Put in pan over graham cracker crumbs.
Place cherries over top. Chill before serving.

title: steak-potato casserole
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces and season.
Peel and slice potatoes and onion.
Alternate layers of steak, potatoes and onion in a covered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jellied shrimp and pineapple salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add egg, vinegar and cream. Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Chill. Sprinkle gelatin on cold water.
Drain pineapple; measure 1/2 cup syrup.
Heat; add to gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves. Add chilled dressing mixture; mix well.
Add drained pineapple and all remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into one large (six cup) mold or individual molds if preferred.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
Garnish with whole shrimp.
Serves six to eight.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie(diabetic recipe)
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Add margarine.
Pour into prepared pie crust, unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: squash-zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and cut squash and zucchini into 1/2-inch slices.
Simmer in water for 10 minutes; drain well.
Combine in bowl the squash and zucchini, butter, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder and 1/2 milk; mix well.
Slowly add eggs and fold into the mixture.
Pour mixture into a well-greased medium casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese evenly on top.
Drizzle remaining milk evenly; let casserole rest in refrigerator for 20 minutes. Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika just before baking.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon-spice dessert dip
directions: Combine cheese and honey, beat until smooth.
Beat in sour cream, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Refrigerate, covered, one to two hours to blend.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Boil, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, without stirring 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla; mix well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3/4 cup sugar with oleo; add pretzels.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (no longer); cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and remaining sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.

title: molasses cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat together molasses, sugar, egg and oil. Sift flour together with spices; mix well and add to first mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Make into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: trash
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and melt in microwave, approximately 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over Crispix in a large bowl.
Pour 1/2 box powdered sugar in a large bag.
Dump all your mixture into the bag, shake gently to mix.
Pour rest of the powdered sugar into bag and again shake gently until all is completely mixed.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and granulated sugar in bowl with hand.
Mix oats, brown sugar, nuts, flour and salt in separate bowl.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan the cranberry and sugar mixture. Spread oat mixture over top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Wonderful served on Thanksgiving.

title: no peek boneless roast
directions: Cut roast into 1-inch cubes.
Salt and pepper.
Brown roast in small amount of oil.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into roaster.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Do not peek.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: sugar free applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins,
together thoroughly, then add raisins. Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam.

title: cajun barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet. Add onion and next 9 ingredients. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add shrimp. Cook 2 minutes. Add remaining 1/2 cup butter and chicken broth. Cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in beer and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat. Remove shrimp from skillet. Mound rice in skillet and arrange shrimp around rice.

title: texi-cali casserole
directions: Brown beef until all pink is gone.
Drain well; blot with paper towel.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir.
Add soups and corn; blend well.
Add sour cream and blend.
Place 1/2 of mixture in casserole and 1 cup of chips. Add remaining meat mixture and top with 1 cup of chips.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until edges are bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: wiener hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt jelly and add cocktail hot dogs or small sections of regular hot dogs and heat through.

title: light-as-air waffles
directions: Blend together eggs and oil.
Add buttermilk to oil and egg mixture and blend.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except flour, then sift in the flour.
Mix; knead mixture.
Put in greased bowl and let rise another hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chicken sandwich filling
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss well.
Use as filling for pita bread.

title: can green beans
directions: Put in snapped beans.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes. Put in jars and seal.
(Use the water to fill with beans in which they were cooked.)

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes.
Fry quickly in hot oil until brown.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Melt chocolate and shortening in saucepan. On low heat until melted.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8x8x2-inch pan.
Bake 30-35 min.
Makes 16 2-inch squares.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks and flavoring.
Add food coloring of your choice to butter mixture. Work in flour.
Use a cookie press for desired shape and design. Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Combine cottage cheese and lemon juice in blender.
Blend until creamy.
Add skim milk a tablespoon at a time to desired consistency.
Yield: 1 cup.
Per 1 tablespoon serving: 15 calories, 60 mg sodium and 1 mg cholesterol.
Exchanges:
1 tablespoon free.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter and press into 2-quart dish for crust.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and butter for 15 minutes with mixer.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas and lay over powdered sugar mixture.
Put pineapple over bananas, then spread on the Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Put in refrigerator.

title: fairy dessert
directions: Make jello as directed. Let stand until it starts to jell. Fold in whipped cream and sugar. Fold in pineapple and chill.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: jean's bridal beans
directions: Cook bacon; drain.
Cook pepper and onion in bacon drippings. Add drained tomatoes.
Chop and mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add beans, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Blend thoroughly but do not cook.
Add mushrooms.
Place in greased casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear up spinach.
Chop eggs and bacon.
Mix together and add stuffing mix and onion.
Pour dressing made from first 6 ingredients over spinach mixture.

title: cranberry christmas cake
directions: Blend syrup and cornstarch in saucepan. Stir in pineapple and cranberry sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling. Boil and stir for 1 minute. Fill layers and top of cake.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, milk, eggs and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls about the size of golf balls.
Brown in hot vegetable oil over low heat.
Make sure mixture is moist.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in 9 x 12-inch pan, no deeper than 3-inches. Then layer finely chopped pepper and onion.
Then peas and finely chopped celery.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle sugar evenly, then cheese.
Cover.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Crumble bacon on top.
Several hours before serving, cut into squares the desired serving size.

title: grandma bettie's gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Cream together thoroughly the butter and sugar.
Add the egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses.
Add flour mixture with hot water until mixture is just smooth.
The batter will be very thin.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Remove the pan and cool on a rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Blend in gravy mix, garlic salt, water, and uncooked rice.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Stir in thawed peas. Continue to simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in onions.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: individual frozen fruit salads
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Line muffin cups with paper liners.
Fill muffin cups with fruit mixture and freeze.
Yield:
approximately 3 dozen.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beating well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake slow until set and well browned.
Bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325° or 350°.

title: oriental chicken curry
directions: Put apples, onion and butter in saucepan; saute on low heat until onion is transparent and soft.
Stir in curry, flour, milk and chicken broth.
Cook on low until slightly thickened, stirring frequently.
Add salt, pepper and chicken.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until chicken is heated through.
Divide rice in 4 portions; top with curry mixture.
Serves 4.

title: garlic roasted potato wedges
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Cut each half into 4 wedges.
In 3-quart saucepan, place potato wedges.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to full boil and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender (8 to 12 minutes). Drain.

title: alyssa's chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice into greased casserole dish.
Skin breasts and place over rice.
Mix onion soup mix with can of mushroom soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well; add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in three 4 x 8-inch loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Put frankfurters in hot water, then dry off.
Dip in batter.

title: sherried beef
directions: Cook in a covered dish for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: diabetic banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and add lightly beaten egg.
Blend in flavorings and liquid sweetener.
Add banana.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Dredge raisins and nuts in flour and add to mixture. Mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Prick chicken and pour sauce over it.
Marinate 2 or 3 days, then grill.

title: spanish style chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic, onion and sweet pepper and saute until veggies are limp, about 5 minutes.
Push veggies aside.
Dust chicken with flour and add to skillet.
Brown 5 minutes per side over medium heat.
Remove chicken and set aside. Add sherry and scrape up any browned bits from skillet.
Add chicken broth and thyme.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Simmer half and half with crushed lobster shells and four tablespoons of butter for 15 minutes.
Strain, pressing on shells and reserve liquid.
In a heavy bottom saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons of the butter over medium heat.
Sprinkle in flour and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, keeping heat low so mixture doesn't brown.
Add tomato paste, paprika and nutmeg.
Whisk half and half into butter-flour mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring to thicken. Add lobster meat and sherry.
Simmer gently 5 minutes and season to taste.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: rabbit a la creole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over rabbit. Marinate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 450°.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Stir every 10 minutes. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with party rye bread.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat in mixer for 5 minutes in order ingredients are given. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Add hot water.
Cook
over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Gradually add diluted Carnation milk to cocoa syrup and continue cooking in double boiler 10 minutes.
Stir thoroughly before serving.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry cream muffins(makes 24 muffins)
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream to the egg mixture. Gently fold in blueberries.
Put in 24 lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: garlic soup
directions: In saucepan, heat oil on medium.
Add garlic and saute until soft and golden.
Add chicken broth, water, salt, pepper, bay leaves and jalapeno pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: ferris' gooseberry bread
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Add jam; mix. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add to the creamed mixture, alternating with the milk.
Mix well.
Bake in a well-greased bread pan (5 1/2 x 9-inch) at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn bread out on wire rack to cool.
This bread cuts best when allowed to stand several hours.

title: bridal punch
directions: Add ice cream to a punch bowl.
Add cream soda.
Add vodka. Add frozen strawberries.
Serve in small glasses (plastic if you like).
Enjoy!

title: e-z supper slice
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and strips of cheese.
Cut loaf of bread in half lengthwise.
Butter halves lightly.
Spread mixture over top surface of bread evenly.
Wrap heavy-duty foil around crust side of each half loaf, leaving top uncovered.
Place on a cookie sheet; bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for 25 minutes. Garnish with strips of cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Place cheese to form X's on top of loaf.
Remove from oven and cut into diagonal slices.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces.
Saute onions and sausage for about 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Add to sausage mixture.
Mix well.
Add cheese.

title: dirty pudding
directions: Break Oreos by hand.
Put 1/2 in bottom of dish.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Mix pudding per package; fold in Cool Whip.
Combine both mixtures well; pour over cookies. Top with rest of broken Oreos.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Combine half of the crushed Oreos with the melted butter to make the crust.
Blend and spread into bottom of a rectangular dish.

title: hamburger eggplant casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato soup.
Brown eggplants in little oil until soft.
Layer in casserole dish first with hamburger, then eggplants.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°, covered.
Put cheese in the last 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp dip(for crackers)
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill until ready to serve.

title: cheeseburger pie(quiche)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate or equivalent casserole dish.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Spread in plate/casserole.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth (1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour over hamburger and bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese, then bake for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: spiced white grape juice
directions: Place first 3 ingredients into a piece of cheesecloth.
Tie with string.
Combine white grape juice and water in a Dutch oven. Add spice bag and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove and discard spice bag and stir in lemon juice and sugar.
Serve hot.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix and cocoa.
Add other ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pans (13 x 9-inch or two 9-inch pans). Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center is clean.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with just enough milk to moisten dough to a stiff consistency, but soft enough to spoon.
Dip with tablespoon and drop into deep hot (350°) fat (medium-high).
Cook until golden brown.
Yield: about 18 pups.

title: scalloped potatoes(quick and easy)
directions: Put frozen potatoes in 12 x 18-inch glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Add mix, butter, flour, onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for one hour, covered.
Remove cover; bake until top is brown (about 20 minutes more).
Serves 10.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in the pan you are going to bake cobbler in.
Mix Jiffy mix, sugar and milk together and pour over melted butter. Pour in the peaches.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: wiener wraps
directions: Wrap hot dog slices in bacon and secure with toothpick. Arrange in single layer in a baking dish and sprinkle brown sugar over the top. Bake at 350° until bacon is done and sugar is melted.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease 9 x 13 pan.
Cut chilies in half; lay out flat on bottom of pan.
Cover chilies with half the tortillas, half tomatoes and half cheeses.
Repeat for second layer.
Beat eggs and spices; pour on top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 40 minutes, uncovered, until knife inserted comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add leeks and saute until they begin to soften, 3-5 minutes.
Add stock & potatoes, bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.

title: carrot cake with orange glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil and sugar well.
Separately sift together:
flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Blend half of the dry ingredients into the sugar and oil, then blend in the other half alternately with 4 eggs, beating one at a time.
Mix thoroughly into batter, the carrots and pecans.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan and bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Split cake horizontally in 3 layers. Spread Orange Glaze between layers and on top.

title: venison salad
directions: Using a food processor or blender, shred about 1 pound of deer (venison).
Cuts best if cold. Put your egg on to hard-boil.
Dice celery and onions.
Combine in bowl.
Add sweet relish, mayonnaise, parsley, diced egg and add meat.
Stir and add salt and pepper to taste.
Great on buns or toasted bread.

title: microwave onions
directions: Peel and wash onions.
Remove some of the center.
Place pat of butter in hole.
Roll up 1 strip bacon and push down into center of onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in microwave dish and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Taste great!

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Crush Doritos, place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan saving some to sprinkle on top.
Pour chicken mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese and Doritos.

title: beef and vegetable stew
directions: Remove any bits of fat from the meat. Heat the oil in a large pot over medium high heat. Saute the meat in the oil for 10 minutes, or until browned on all sides. Remove meat and set aside. Add the onion and tomato paste to the pot and saute over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until onion is tender, stirring often. Return the meat to the skillet along with the beef broth, combining with the onion and tomato paste mixture. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender. Add the carrots, potatoes, rosemary, thyme, bay leaf and crushed red pepper flakes and simmer, covered, for another 45 minutes. (Note: It may be necessary to add some water if the stew seems too thick.) Finally, add the mushrooms and the peas and allow stew to heat through, about another 10 to 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf and rosemary sprig before serving.

title: divinity candy
directions: Microwave on HIGH 2 minutes. Stir with wooden spoon. Remove.

title: rice pudding(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In a large pot, heat milk and rice over medium heat for one hour, stirring.
In another bowl, mix eggs, cream and sugar.
Add this to the pot after one hour.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes or cucumber and onions thin; cover with water then add lime and let stand 24 hours. Wash 4 or 5 times; add vinegar, sugar, and spices and cook until clear, about 1 hour over slow heat. Pack in sterilized jars; cover with hot liquid and seal.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: Add cream-style corn.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk and grated cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and chowder is heated through. Do not boil.
Serves 4.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as directed on box.
Add ingredients as listed, beating hard after each directed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Set ice cream out to get room temperature.
Make Jell-O with boiling water, add ice cream.
Add remaining ingredients and put in a Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Nice for the holidays!

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large container with a tight lid.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour marinade over vegetables and toss; cover.
Chill at least 3 hours. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: rosie's soft brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough flour to roll.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: golden carrot cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together and stir in the flour, salt, baking powder and coconut.
Drop 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Frost with Orange Butter Frosting.

title: russian rocks
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Cover bowl and chill.
Roll dough and slice.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 300°.

title: christmas stew (for scent)
directions: Cover with water and simmer on stove for a fresh scent.

title: microwave rotel cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Put in microwave until cheese melts, stirring often.
Enjoy!

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well and blend in the unsalted butter until mixture resembles meal. In a bowl, combine the buttermilk and lightly beaten egg.
Stir this mixture into the flour mixture and form into a ball.
Knead the dough lightly on a floured surface until it is smooth.
Transfer it to a buttered baking sheet and form it into an 8-inch round.
Cut a 1/2-inch deep X in the center of the loaf with a shape knife dipped in flour.
Cut should come to within 1-inch of edges.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Transfer to a rack and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: coconut biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, coconut, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender (or 2 knives) to form coarse crumbs.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix with fork until particles are moistened and cling together.
Drop tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 16 biscuits.

title: magical biscuits
directions: Measure flour into bowl and make a well.
Pour into the "well" (only after shaking up good) the whipping cream.
Stir with a fork.
Roll out as usual and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Arrange bacon slices over bean mixture.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, about 1 hour.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 12-inch pan; use your hand to spread evenly.
Bake 15 minutes (or until browned some) at 350°.
Cool in refrigerator, then add filling.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain canned fruits.
Cut peach halves in two pieces. Arrange fruits in a 2 qt. shallow casserole dish.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, molasses, ginger, curry and butter.
Dot fruit with small dabs of topping.
Heat fruit at 350° for 35-45 minutes. Good with ham or chicken.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form into balls. Melt chocolate chips and wax until melted. Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper. Cool.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate.
This sauce is particularly good with ham or cold turkey.
It also may be used as an appetizer poured over a block of cream cheese and served with crackers. Yields 1 pint.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl; do not cook macaroni.
Let stand overnight in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before you bake it, add the crushed potato chips over the top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Very good.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In separate bowl, mix flour alternately with sour cream.
Add soda and vanilla. Beat 1 minute longer.
Use 1/4 stick butter to coat Bundt pan and dust with flour.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn immediately onto plate.

title: spinach and corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan and bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven (or 13 to 14 minutes in microwave at 70%).

title: jalapeno appetizer
directions: In a quiche dish or 9-inch pie pan, layer the relish (or salsa), 1 cup Cheddar cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, then 1 cup Cheddar again. Beat the eggs and milk. Pour over the layered items. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs, molasses and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to shortening mixture.
Fold in oats, raisins and walnuts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: crullers
directions: Beat eggs; add cream and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and combine with liquid using just enough flour that can be rolled but still soft.
Mix well and let stand for 2 hours.
Turn out on floured board and roll to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips, 6-inches by 1-inch.
Fry in deep fat fryer at 360° until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken chip bake
directions: Combine all these ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Pile lightly in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, then with chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: texas sheet cake(very good!!!)
directions: Sift sugar and flour.
Bring shortening, oleo, water and cocoa to a boil.
Pour this over the mixture of flour and sugar.
Mix together well and add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and salt. Pour into a greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies with penuche frosting
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together until well blended.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Mix in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.
Frost with Penuche Frosting.
Makes about 7 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water, raisins and orange and lemon juices.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Set aside to cool.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Pour in cooled raisin filling.
Put top crust on and seal and crimp.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Make tiny slits in top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: basic yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup water.
In a separate bowl, pour 2 cups hot water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Combine dry milk with 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Stir into hot water mixture, beating well.
Add yeast water and enough of remaining flour to form soft dough.
When mixture begins to pull away from sides of pan, turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Form dough into a ball.
Let rest on kneading surface or in a greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper or a damp cloth.
Let dough rise until it doubles in size, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stovepipes(an authentic italian recipe)
directions: Fry ground beef, scrambled until brown.
Combine browned ground beef, tomatoes and tomato paste and cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cranberry ring salad
directions: Wash cranberries.
Add to 1 cup of water and cook until tender. Add sugar and cook 5 minutes more.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Dissolve in hot cranberries and add pinch of salt.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts, celery and grapes; mix thoroughly.
Pour into oiled ring mold and chill until firm.
Serve on bed of chicory or lettuce.

title: "not your mama's banana puddin"
directions: Use about 9 x 13 pan (glass prettier). Layer cookies, then sliced bananas. Make pudding and mix with cream cheese and Eagle Brand. Layer this. Can add more bananas, but top with another layer of cookies. Very pretty. Refrigerate, then serve.

title: kathy's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Saute onion and garlic in Pam sprayed skillet.
Add mushrooms, soup and cheese.
Heat thoroughly.
Add broccoli.
Mix well.
Place in an ovenproof pan.
Melt margarine.
Add crumbled crackers.
Stir until crackers have been coated with margarine.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini gumbo
directions: Mix tomatoes, chunks of zucchini, onion and garlic; cook until boils.
Add celery last; cook until almost tender.

title: one dish italian chicken
directions: Put all ingredients into a pan in one layer.
Pour cooking wine over everything.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes and onions are done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 70 balls. Freezes well.

title: spinach bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan, remove.
In large bowl beat eggs, add flour, milk, garlic salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add cheese and spinach.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy stir-fry
directions: Add oil and vegetables to hot skillet or wok; saute until vegetables are almost tender (3 to 5 minutes).
Add rice, meat and soy sauce and mix well.
Lower heat and stir in beaten eggs.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes more, remove from heat and let set for 2 to 3 minutes (or until eggs are done).
Additional soy sauce can be added to taste.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, shortening and molasses.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Beat until well blended. One cup of chopped raisins may be added to batter.
Pour into well-oiled pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beefy mushroom cube steak
directions: Wash well cured ham in hot water, scrubbing well to remove pepper, etc. with stiff brush. Rinse well and place ham in deep pan.
Completely cover with cold water.
Soak at least 24 hours, changing water at least four or five times during soaking period to remove salt.
Place ham in large kettle, completely covering with cold water.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and boil gently for 30 minutes per pound.
When time is up, test with a fork.
If tender, remove from water and place cut side down on baking sheet. Remove skin and trim fat.
Remove any loose bone.
Score fat on top of ham, being sure to cut down in fat but not the lean portion.
Place whole cloves in decorative pattern completely covering scored top.
Sift brown sugar over the top and place in 400° oven until sugar melts.
Place on platter and cool completely before slicing.

title: sue's ice cream
directions: Cook ingredients, except vanilla, until it coats a spoon. Cool for a while and add vanilla and milk or enough to fill your freezer can.
You can add fresh peaches, bananas or strawberries. Delicious.

title: meatballs
directions: Make into balls and place in a casserole dish.

title: easy jellyroll
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan and line with waxed paper; grease and flour waxed paper.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, baking powder and salt; beat at high speed of mixer until foamy. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Fold in flour and lemon extract.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar in a 15 x 10-inch rectangle on a linen towel.
When cake is done, immediately loosen from sides of pan and turn out on sugar. Peel off paper; starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together.
Cool on a wire rack, seam side down, for 10 minutes. Unroll cake; remove towel.
Spread cake with jelly and re-roll. Place on serving plate, seam side down.
May garnish with strawberries and cream.

title: "porcupine" meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place in a single layer of 2-quart casserole. Combine soup and water and pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean dish
directions: Cook ground beef and onion a little together. Then mix all other ingredients together in a baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy bread dip
directions: Cut top off 1 loaf of bread, saving top for use as a lid. Hollow out this loaf, saving the insides for dipping later. Combine all the other ingredients and stuff the hollowed out bread; replace top.
Wrap tightly in foil and bake approximately 1 hour at 375°.
Cut up reserved loaf of bread and insides for dipping.
Serve hot with the pieces of bread all around.
Don't forget to eat the shell when cheese mixture is gone.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: Combine ham and onions.
Place about 1/3 cup down the center of each tortilla.
Top with 2 Tbsp. cheese.
Roll up and place seam side down in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
In a bowl, combine flour, cream, eggs and salt.
Pour over tortillas.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes. Uncover, bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake for 3 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
You can test for doneness by sticking knife in egg mixture.
If knife comes out clean, it is done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 275° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked macaroni
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper. Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with onion rings and remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a loaf pan.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into pie crust (it will be heaping).
Roll out remaining crust and cover pie.
Tuck top crust down and over bottom pie crust.
Cut vents.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 60 minutes.
You may need to put tinfoil over pie 40 minutes after in oven to keep from burning.

title: quick and easy barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in electric skillet, salt and pepper.
Add garlic, onions and pepper.
Pour catsup over chicken, onions and pepper, then cover with Coke.
Bake at 325° in electric skillet approximately 1 hour or until liquid is almost gone.

title: scalloped eggs
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter; add flour and whisk.
Add half and half and milk; bring to a boil slowly.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add cheese, celery and seasonings; stir until cheese melts.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, alternate layers of sauce, bacon and eggs. Top with 1/3 package Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix tossed with 4 to 6 tablespoons of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell, bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add wet ingredients and mix well. Can be kept in refrigerator for 6 weeks, using as needed.
Bake in muffin tins with papers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar and nutmeg.
Blend in shortening.
Add flour alternately with milk, using only enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead gently for 30 seconds.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat until brown, about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain well. While warm, coat with granulated sugar or confectioners sugar. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: neiman-marcus cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add to butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place two inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for six minutes at 375°.
May require a few more minutes than six, depending on how your oven bakes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop and steam head of cabbage.
Drain.
Place 1/2 of cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 can of water chestnuts, 1/4 cup of sour cream and 1/4 cup of cheese.
Repeat another layer.
Bake, covered, at 350° for approximately 10 minutes until mixture is bubbly and cheese begins to melt.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Cut sourdough bread into chunks making sure that each piece has one side of crust for spearing and dipping.
Rub an electric fry pan or saucepan with the cut garlic.
Heat the garlic and wine in the pan.
Grate the cheese (Gruyere and Emmenthaler is a good mix.)
Toss together with cornstarch.
Remove the garlic from the wine; gradually fork stir handfuls of cheese.
Mix in slowly so it stays hot.

title: holiday punch (slush)
directions: Thaw juices.
Mix juices and powdered sugar together in a blender until mixed.
Pour in large container.
Add Squirt and gin.
Mix well.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Thaw for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: hot chocolate milk mix
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Use about 1/3 cup mix per cup of hot water.

title: my mother's applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add egg and applesauce.
(Do not use mixer.)
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture. Add cinnamon, nutmeg and raisins before stirring in flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325°.
Serves 15 plus.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix gelatin, cold water and boiling water.
Add well drained vegetables to gelatin, then add mayonnaise and salt.
Refrigerate overnight or until spreadable consistency.
Makes large amount.

title: microwave chili pork chops
directions: Shake seasoning mix and flour in a plastic bag.
Place each pork chop into the bag and shake to coat with mixture.
Place seasoned chops in a microwave browning dish or 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on Medium-high for 12 minutes.
Turn chops over and rotate dish; microwave on Medium-high for 12 minutes or until chops are done.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve hot.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Mix mustard, flour, salt and egg, adding some milk and melted butter in cooking pan.
When hot, add cheese; stir until smooth. Add milk to thin to right texture.
Serve with toast points. Makes 6 servings.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown meat and add rest of ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook for 4 hours and serve.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix orange juice, butter, vanilla wafers and powdered sugar until well blended. Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut. Serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan. Layer on top with potatoes, sliced onion and cover with soup. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: baked cabbage and franks
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of water for 5 minutes until fairly tender.
Drain and turn into buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the salt and cover with the franks.
Make a smooth white sauce with butter, flour and milk. Stir in mustard and remaining salt.
Pour over casserole mix. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Combine melted butter with sugar. Add sour cream. Blend well. Add eggs; beat well. Stir in all remaining dry ingredients until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake in 9-inch greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Done when tester comes out clean and cake springs back.
Turn out onto plate. Dust with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer together the first 6 ingredients in a skillet until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in a large casserole dish or Dutch oven.
Cover the container and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: working man's stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Dump the remaining ingredients into the pan or crock-pot (do not drain vegetables). Cook over low heat. The longer the stew simmers, the more the flavors blend.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump pineapple (undrained) into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherry layer. Sprinkle nuts over cake.
Cut up butter over layered mix evenly. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Good with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked seasoned rice
directions: Place rice, vegetables and seasonings in a casserole dish and mix thoroughly.
Add broth and water; stir.
Place dish in oven, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: all-in-one meat casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Season to taste.
Spread evenly in large casserole.
Drain whole corn and spread over meat; likewise with cream-style corn, then the mashed potatoes.
Top with the onion rings and heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well; form a ball.
Roll in pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello with water; let cool.
Mix with Cool Whip and strawberries.
Put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: chocolate prune cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, chocolate and cinnamon together.
Add alternately with milk. Add prunes and beat well.
Add soda.
Bake in 350° oven (for two 9-inch round pans, bake for 25 minutes or for 9 x 13-inch pan bake for about 45 minutes).
Save about 4 prunes for frosting.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Squeeze moisture out of thawed spinach (do not cook).
Cook sliced zucchini just until tender; drain.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, grated carrots, eggs, nutmeg, garlic powder and parsley.
Mix well.

title: chicken ala cornflakes
directions: Wash and drain chicken.
Place on paper towel.
Pour cup of milk in bowl; dip chicken in milk.
Place on plate and season with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Roll chicken in crushed cornflakes and place on slightly greased pan; bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until nicely brown.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well until all combined.
Blend in mashed bananas.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Divide batter in half; add cocoa to half.
Spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon remaining batter on top and swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well.
Heat in greased casserole dish in 350° oven for 20 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Serve with Tostitos.
Serves 12.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well, add sour milk and beat well.
Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and soda.
Stir in nuts. Bake in wax paper lined 5 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam cheese dip
directions: Saute until soft the green pepper, onion and butter.
Take off burner and add cayenne, Worcestershire sauce, milk, catsup, cheese and clams.
Serve warm.
Great with chips and bread.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan(s) of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mary mccarthy's cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and flour.
Divide into 4 balls.
Chill.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour 3/4 cup of broth from chicken into dish.
Spoon on can of drained, mixed vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Top with the butter, flour and milk mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 6-8.

title: santa's irish cream liqueur(in honor of "la paloma")
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Serve over ice, if desired.
Store in decanter, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Stir before serving.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water in saucepan until raisins are tender and water is absorbed.
Combine sugar substitute, 2 tablespoons water, oil, flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and pecans. Mix in applesauce.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake a pie crust and allow it to cool.
Mix dry ingredients, then add water.
Cook on the stove until it becomes a clear red (not milky).
Let cool and pour over strawberries that have been placed in the cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: pull apart rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Pour hot water over sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Add 1/2 cup flour, mixing thoroughly. Stir in dissolved yeast and add egg. Beat thoroughly. Add enough flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured board and let rest 10 minutes. Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise until doubled. Shape into 16 round rolls. Place 8 in 9-inch greased round cake pan. Repeat. Let rise. Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Brush tops with melted butter when they come out of the oven.

title: cheese squares
directions: Put chilies and cheese in lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Pour beaten eggs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Very rich and full of cholesterol but real good.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Boil liquid and spices for 5 minutes.
Put tomatoes into pint jars.
Pour hot liquid over tomatoes and seal.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: baked red potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes into small pieces.
Coat potatoes with olive oil lightly.
Sprinkle Italian dressing and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pink pears
directions: Place pears cut side down in large skillet.
Add 1 cup soda pop.
Cover and simmer until pears are tender 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into liquid in skillet after removing pears and placing one pear in each dessert dish cut side up.
Cook liquid mixture, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into pear half.
Pour 1/2 cup remaining pop into Cool Whip.
Mix to color.
Top each pear. Serves 8. Makes 65 calories.

title: creamy strawberry frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and butter.
Stir in vanilla, milk and strawberries.
Beat until smooth.
Frost cake and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: lemon balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at
a
time.
Add lemon extract.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add
to
other ingredients.
Roll into round small balls the size of marbles. Cook in 350° oven until done.

title: pizza cake
directions: Mix cookie mix as directed and put in pizza pan.
Bake and then cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread on cookie mix.
Arrange fruit slices on top.

title: christmas cider
directions: Simmer cider 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Stir good. Simmer until hot and serve.

title: cheese garden casserole
directions: *These are weight measurements.

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolk slightly; add cream. Add to dry ingredients slowly.
Add vinegar slowly.
If added too fast, it will curdle.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (soft custard).
Serve warm.

title: angel food pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in hot water and cook until clear and thick.
