Pour while hot over beaten egg whites. Add nuts and coconut.
Beat well.
Cool and pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover the top with whipped cream.

title: nathan's hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Dip out batter with small ice cream scoop.
Deep fry.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients into a spread.
Split open rolls; spread half of roll with prepared spread.
Place ham on spread. Put small piece of cheese on ham.
Put top of roll back on. Return rolls to foil container and cover with foil.
Bake at 400° only until cheese melts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir together corn, sugar, salt, flour and eggs.
Mix melted margarine with milk and pour into corn mixture.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish in 350° preheated oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until thick and put in refrigerator.
With mixer, cream together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and butter.
Then add with mixer Cool Whip, pudding and vanilla to cheese mixture.
Layer in bowl 1/3 crushed cookies, 1/2 pudding mix, 1/3 crushed cookies and 1/2 pudding mixture.
Cover with remaining cookies and refrigerate.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until needed.

title: butterscotch chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, butter and cocoa.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well, then take off the stove.
With teaspoon place on wax paper to cool. They harden as they cool.

title: grilled p. b. and j.
directions: Make a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.
(I like to put peanut butter on both pieces and jelly in the middle.)
Put butter on outside and grill in a pan like you would for a grilled cheese.

title: vanilla cream pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in pan.
Set aside.
Beat egg and add milk.
Stir into cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cook and stir one minute longer.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Chill before serving. Makes about 6 servings of 1/3 cup each.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, milk, egg and crackers; mix well. Place in a loaf pan and make a groove down the center of loaf. Combine in a bowl the catsup, water, mustard and brown sugar. Pour over meat; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rump roast
directions: Coat roast
with
mixture
of
flour,
salt and pepper. Brown roast in
12-inch
Dutch
oven with oil.
Mix broth, bay leaves, garlic salt,
marjoram
and basil.	Pour over meat and bake 2 1/2 hours.
You
can
remove meat when done and thicken juices with flour for gravy.

title: people's puppy chow
directions: Melt first three ingredients together over low heat.
Spread cereal in shallow pan. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Place coated cereal in paper bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: high jump ham pockets
directions: Mix ham, pineapple, cheese, bell pepper, mayonnaise and onion. Fill bread with spinach and ham mixture.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain, transfer to bowl.
Mash and add sour cream, cream cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Gradually beat in enough milk to make smooth and fluffy.
Turn into greased casserole.
Cover with foil.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Bake uncovered at 350°.
Dot with margarine.
Cook 45 to 55 minutes until heated through.
Yum!

title: pork chop hawaiian
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown chops slowly in hot shortening. Drain off drippings.
Mix applesauce and cinnamon.
Pour over chops.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: cape cod scallops
directions: Wash scallops, then drain on paper towel.
Prepare crumbs from French bread by cutting up into small pieces or blend lightly in blender.
Put crumbs into a pan with melted butter or margarine. Add parsley, tarragon, salt and lemon juice to the buttered crumbs. Stir this mixture thoroughly.
Add scallops and coat with mixture. Put scallop mixture into a shallow dish; bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Run under broiler to brown.
Serves 2.

title: corn-zucchini bake(very versatile - good for barbecues to formal dinners!)
directions: Wash zucchini; do not pare.
Slice about 1-inch thick.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Drain and mash with fork.
Cook onion in the first tablespoon of butter or margarine until tender.
Combine beaten eggs, mashed zucchini, onion, corn, Swiss cheese and salt.
Turn into a 1-quart round or square casserole baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Place on baking sheet.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Melt margarine in pan. Pour peaches mixed with sugar in pan.
Pour batter over top of fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter and sugar together and cook about 12 minutes or until light brown.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool. Melt chocolate over hot water.
Spread on candy.
Let stand, then turn candy over and put rest of chocolate on the other side. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
In place of the cold water, add the strawberries.
Chill until partially thickened.
Stir in angel food cake (torn into bite-size pieces).
Pour into 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: marshmallow cookies
directions: Melt caramels, milk and oleo in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip marshmallow in caramel mixture, tap to remove excess and roll in Rice Krispies.
Place on cookie sheet to cool, then put them in a cupcake paper liner.

title: divinity candy
directions: In a very heavy pan, boil sugar, syrup, water and salt to hard-boil stage. Test by dropping into cold water. Pour mixture into egg whites gradually while beating at high speed for 5 minutes. Mixture becomes stiff and forms a peak. Drop quickly by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Garnish with pecan halves or drained maraschino cherries.

title: prime rib
directions: Place meat on rack in oven pan-fat side up.
Rub meat with seasonings.
Turn oven up to 425°. Cook for 15 minutes, to sear meat.
Turn oven down to 325° and cook 20 minutes for each pound of meat.
Do not
cover with foil while cooking.
Slice to thickness desired.
Ends well to rare in middle of meat, can cook longer if desire well done throughout.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Put everything in a large mixer bowl.
Beat 10 minutes (time by clock and beat 10 full minutes).
Pour into tube pan (or Bundt pan).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300° (or 1 1/4 hours at 325°).

title: gramma ritchey's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add pumpkin to which baking soda has been added.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet and spread thin (use glass with a cloth stretched over the bottom and held in place with a rubber band). Dip glass into cold water before pushing on dough.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: In a large heavy kettle, mix together the sugar, butter, syrup, milk and pulp.
Cook to soft ball stage (235°).
Allow to cool and add salt and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: cheese danish(low calorie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Spray tortillas with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle each tortilla with scant 1/2 teaspoon sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Turn over.
Do other sides.
Cut each tortilla into 4 wedges.
Stand rounded edge of each tortilla wedge in bottom of muffin tin by curling in sides. Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned and crispy; cool.

title: rummy rice pudding
directions: Soak raisins in rum. Cook rice according to package directions. Mix all other ingredients in a bowl. Add raisins and rum. When rice is cooked, add it to mixture and mix well. Refrigerate for a few hours. Serve as is or with heavy cream, whipped cream or a whipped topping.

title: large custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nutmeg and crust.
Pour into 10-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 375°; bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Insert knife; pie is done if knife comes out clean.

title: grace's apricot salad
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1 large package cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Put in refrigerator until mixture starts to jell.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: texas pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortillas; roll like a jelly roll.
Place, seam side down, in a storage container.
Chill overnight.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Pick over and clean salmon, saving liquid.
Saute onion and celery in butter in bottom of 4-quart soup kettle until tender. Add soup and milk.
Stir in corn, salmon and reserved salmon liquid.
Heat through and top with butter.

title: four day sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making one 9 x 13-inch layer.
When cool, split layer and make 2 layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill. Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers.

title: manhattan potatoes
directions: Peel, dice and boil potatoes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove lid and bake 15 minutes more.

title: ham skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients except cheese. Mix well.
Heat to boiling. Cover and simmer 18 to 20 minutes. (Stir occasionally) or until noodles are done.
Stir in cheese. Heat until cheese begins to melt.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pie dough #3
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Using a pastry blender or your fingertips, work shortening into flour mixture until resulting crumbs are about the size of dried split peas.
Store in tightly covered container.
(Empty shortening can with plastic lid may be used.)
Mixture does not have to be refrigerated; can be kept as long as 4 months.

title: polish potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes (use grated, not blender).
In
a large bowl, stir all ingredients together.
Add olive oil to large skillet.
Oil should be very hot.
Form into cakes.
Brown evenly on both sides.
Serve, if desired, with sour cream or stewed tomatoes.
Makes 12 to 16 cakes.

title: best fruitcake ever
directions: Before you begin, sample the whiskey to check for quality. Good isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the whisky again as it must be just right.
To be sure the whiskey is of the highest quality, pour 1 level cup into a gllass & drink as gast as you can.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 tsp. thugar and meat again.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Place first four ingredients in a double boiler, mix and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from stove and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in coconut to taste.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in a glass of warm water.
Let it rise double, about 3 1/2 hours.
Mix all ingredients together and knead.
Roll out dough, and cut dough with biscuit cutter.
Let biscuits rise double again.
Put on a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes until light brown on top.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Brown hamburger, with salt.
Add onions and other ingredients.
Let simmer until warmed.
Add a little water if it is too thick.
Extra brown sugar can be added also if you like.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables. Combine in a large bowl.
In a quart jar, combine remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake.
Pour over beans and mix all together gently. Chill and serve.

title: calico casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (with half the cheese).
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, salt and pepper; shape into very small balls.
Combine chili sauce, lemon juice and grape jelly and place in a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add uncooked meatballs and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover from pan the last 30 minutes of baking.
Transfer to chafing dish and serve hot with toothpicks.
Yield:
30 to 40 meatballs.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onions and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Shape into small meatballs and brown in the margarine. Place in a casserole dish and combine the preserves and the barbecue sauce and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach; add water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir again before serving.
Cut out center of Hawaiian bread and pour spinach dip into center.
Tear bread that you took from loaf into pieces and use for dipping.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, water and sour cream. Mix on medium speed for at least 2 minutes. Stir in chocolate and chips. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli, cauliflower and carrots
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine last four ingredients and mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix up every so often.
Chill 6 hours.

title: tom's tantalizing truly terrific turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
(Best to use meat thermometer at 170°.)

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and serve with potato chips or fresh vegetables.

title: low-fat spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles for doneness. Drain and rinse in hot water.

title: orange punch delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well. Serve over ice.

title: squash pie
directions: Put squash into blender and add other ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, cut part of cheese into 20 to 24 (1/2-inch) cubes.
Shred the rest; set aside.
In large bowl with fork, mix well all the ingredients except salad oil and spaghetti sauce.
Shape some mixture around each cheese cube to make 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: golden brownies
directions: Heat sugar and butter in pan; do not boil.
Let cool, then add beaten egg and cream well.
Add flour, baking powder, chopped nuts, vanilla and chips. Bake in greased square pan at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut up radishes, celery and pickles to bite size.
Cook and peel potatoes.
Mix mustard, Miracle Whip and pickle juice.
Mix with potatoes, radishes and celery.
Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash the cooked or canned potatoes with the beaten eggs. Continue mixing with the brown sugar and softened butter until fairly smooth.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over pecans/coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, margarine, cream cheese and vanilla (margarine and cream cheese may be softened in microwave).
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cake will look soft when removed from oven.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large, glass bowl.
Microwave for 5 minutes or until boils.
Take out and stir ingredients, then return to microwave and cook 3 minutes longer.

title: yvonne's potent long island ice tea
directions: Blend in ice and lemon wedges.
Drop in lemon slices.
Serve immediately.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour over corn flakes and stir until well coated. Shape into wreaths and add 2 or 3 candies for berries.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: nita's green beans
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around 3 or 4 green beans.
Continue until all bacon is used.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add garlic salt and brown sugar to melted butter.
Caramelize and mix well. Pour mixture over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Cook salt pork, onion, tomato and garlic in vegetable oil over medium heat.
Stir frequently until onion is tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in rice and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in boiling water. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer.
Cover 10 minutes.
Remove cover and cool, stirring frequently until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy, 15 to 18 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine the flour, butter and chopped pecans.
Press in bottom of dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate in water; stir.
In large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add flour to mixture alternately with buttermilk until blended.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine fruits and set aside.
In small bowl, combine dry pudding, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until blended.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in fruit and chill.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Slice sausage in 1-inch pieces. Cook with water and sauerkraut for about 1 hour; drain. Layer half of the potatoes, sauerkraut (with sausage), cheese and remaining potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar
and oil.
Add dry ingredients. Add berry
mixture
and mix until blended.
Pour in 2 greased and floured bread pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake 1 hour or until done. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then on rack.

title: bonnie's biscuits
directions: Sift flour into bowl along with Bakewell cream and soda. Blend in shortening; add milk all at once.
Roll out on lightly floured
board, cut with biscuit cutter and bake in preheated oven at 500° for approximately 5 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or put in crock-pot for a minimum of 4 hours.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil for 15 minutes.
Cool and shred into a buttered casserole dish.
In a heavy saucepan, mix remaining ingredients together over low heat and stir until cheese is melted and sauce is heated through.
Do not boil.
(Can do this in microwave.)
Pour mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with paprika. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing as directed on package. Then mix all together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked rice
directions: Put all the ingredients in a 2-quart, covered casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When cooking, cover with aluminum foil.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Over medium heat, melt butter and chocolate chips; add milk. Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon (use measuring spoon around each Kiss), covering completely.
Put 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Cookies will be soft and shiny but will become firm as they cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls into 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix package of dressing, cream cheese and Miracle Whip together.
Spread over rolled crescent dough. Cut into squares.
Sprinkle vegetables and Cheddar cheese over top.

title: bea's pickles
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to each jar, bring brine to boil. Pour over
cold
pack
cucumbers
with dill, garlic and a hot pepper (optional).
Put
in
hot
bath until cucumbers change color. These stay crisp for a long time.

title: cole slaw for freezing
directions: Mix salt with cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture and add carrot and pepper.
When boiled mixture has cooled, pour over slaw mix.
Put into containers and freeze until ready to use.
May be refrozen.

title: chicken fajita dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir and place in microwave for 4 minutes. Remove and serve with chips.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter until creamy. Gradually beat in peanut butter, then brown sugar, then granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs, then vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour and baking soda; gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Press balls down with a fork, making a crisscross pattern on top of each with fork tines.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool on baking sheets for about a minute, then transfer to racks and let cool completely.
Store airtight.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over bottom of greased pan.

title: aunt bonnie's apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cover with glaze while still warm.

title: olive-nut spread
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers or fresh bread.

title: nippy cheese sticks
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature.
Grate cheese and combine with other ingredients (use hands, well washed).
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness between waxed paper and cut with a shaped cutter or into thin strips with a sharp knife.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Stores well in freezer or coffee can with plastic lid or large tin.

title: lynell's fabulous punch
directions: Boil 7 cups of water and 2 cups sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 2 cups of water with 4 green tea bags and let cool with tea bags still in the water.
When both mixtures are cool, mix together and add the lemonade and orange juice (both undiluted) and brandy.
Put in large container and freeze for at least 48 hours.
Fill glasses half full with frozen slush and fill to the top with 7-Up.

title: joggin-in-a-jug
directions: Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.
Drink 2 ounces each day.

title: old fashioned hot spiced tea
directions: Boil for 20 minutes in a large pan.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 drops of red food coloring and 2 drops of cinnamon oil.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut immediately.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except enough buttered crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour into large baking dish and cook about 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with buttered crumbs and cook a little longer.

title: shrimp kebabs with honey-mustard glaze
directions: You will need 12 bamboo skewers, soaked for 30 minutes in water.

title: old fashioned rye bread(roy broyd)
directions: Dissolve yeast in small amount of lukewarm water.
Add the water, molasses, sugar, salt, shortening and rye flour to the yeast; beat until bubbly.
Add enough white flour to make dough stiff enough to knead.
Knead dough until it springs back.
Put in greased bowl and set in warm place.
When double in bulk, knead again and let rise again.
When light, shape into 4 loaves and rise again.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Mix together broccoli, green peppers, onions and Cheddar cheese.
Spread in a greased 11 x 15-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix with beater the eggs, milk, water, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli layer.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy homemade salsa(medium)
directions: Empty can of Ro-Tel into medium bowl.
Add diced tomato, onion, garlic, pepper and tomato sauce into bowl.
Stir, squeeze in lemon; refrigerate.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in honey and let set about 10 minutes.
Add wheat flour, shortening and salt to yeast mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn
out on lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 5 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease top.
Cover with cloth and place in warm place until double, 20 minutes. Punch down, divide in half.
Shape into loaves and let rise again, about 40 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut the chicken into one inch pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, green pepper, and garlic in the oil in a dutch oven until the chicken loses its pink color.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes about 9 cups of stew

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: hot white chocolate
directions: Heat milk and combine all ingredients.
Stir 3 minutes or until melted.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 cups.

title: sonja's cheese potatoes
directions: Heat milk, cheeses and margarine until melted.
Pour over 2 pound package of hash browns.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Pour over meat and simmer 10 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Roll apple pieces in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; press or roll each to a 4 1/2-inch circle.
Place sugared apple pieces, rounded-side down, on center of each biscuit.
Stretch dough around apple completely covering fruit. Dip each filled biscuit in melted margarine, then in remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place seam-side down in ungreased 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle any remaining cinnamon-sugar over biscuits.
Add water to baking pan.

title: spinach fandango
directions: Brown beef with mushrooms and seasonings. Add spinach and cook until thawed. Drain well. Stir in soup and sour cream. Pour into casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread in 9x13 sprayed pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and scoop out a little of the inside of the cap to make a pocket.
Chop enough stems to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add mushroom caps and toss just long enough to coat them with oil.
Remove and set aside.
Add chopped mushroom stems to skillet and cook over low heat until very soft. Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and ham.
Add egg and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into mushroom caps. Place caps in baking dish and drizzle enough oil over each mushroom to moisten.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 12 to 16.

title: salmon loaf(diabetic recipe)
directions: Spray 7 1/2 x 24 1/4-inch pan with Pam; set aside.
Drain salmon; reserve liquid (save bones and crush for free calcium). Flake salmon; add bones and vinegar.
Add enough water to 1/2 to salmon liquid.
Add all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack into prepared pan; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Leave salmon in pan 5 minutes before unmolding.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Break lettuce.
Cut celery into pieces.
Combine with mayonnaise and peas.
Use 2 forks to mix with.
Cover with Parmesan.
May also add layer of mashed eggs and crumbled bacon.

title: cream pie
directions: Scald 1 cup milk over boiling water. Mix sugar, salt, flour and remaining milk together.
Stir into hot milk and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly. Cover and cook over boiling water for 5 minutes. Add mixture slowly to egg yolk and cook 1 minute longer.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into pastry shell and cover with whipped cream. Makes 1 (8-inch) pie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Leave a little cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of dish.
Add onion soup.
Add water and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Place cut up fryer on top. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Uncover and bake to brown fryer.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix bananas, drained pineapple, strawberries and pecans.
Add to cream cheese mixture. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into a glass 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Take out of freezer for 15 minutes before serving. Cut into squares.

title: linda's hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: baked chicken breasts with gruyere and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Dip pieces in egg and then roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Brown lightly in margarine in a small pan (or can broil for a few minutes each side).
Transfer chicken to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Slice mushrooms over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over mushrooms.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix jello, condensed milk, coconut, nuts, vanilla and red food color.
Let stand a few minutes.
While waiting, dip almond slivers into green food color and spread to dry.
Roll into strawberry-shaped balls.
Drop and roll into sugar crystals. Insert stems.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream cheese with butter in blender.
Add ice water; add flour and seasonings and chill.
Roll out of pastry tube or on a slightly floured board 1/8 inch thick; cut strips 1/2 inch wide, 4 to 5 inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lynda's cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except preserves).
Shape into a ring.
Fill center with preserves.

title: swiss chard soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble; set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add chicken broth and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are about half done.
Now, add chard stems (sliced thinly).
Cook until nearly done and add leaves (chopped finely).
Cook another 5 minutes, then add half and half and salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot and sprinkle bacon on each serving.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Place meats in frying pan, cook slowly, turning until brown. Remove from frying pan; drain well.
Place scallions, onions, peppers and celery in frying pan with small amount of oil.
Simmer slowly for about 5 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Combine and chill 1 1/2 hours.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips and 1/2 square paraffin wax.
Shape dough into balls and roll in chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish salad with pimiento strips.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until melted, then beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with raw vegetables. Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in water, cider and egg.

title: candy apple surprise
directions: Cut apples into 7-Up and water; drain. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Add candy. Mix and pour over apples. Mix well.

title: spaghetti-beef casserole
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet. Add meat, onion and green pepper. Cook until browned. Add soup, water and garlic.
Blend in 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix spaghetti and 1 cup cheese.
Put spaghetti in 3-quart casserole. Top with remaining cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili sauce(century-old recipe)
directions: Cook all ingredients together until the desired thickness is reached.
Store in glass jars.

title: orange ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour a 9-cup Bundt cake pan. Beat baking mix, buttermilk, sugar, baking soda, margarine, eggs, orange peel and vanilla in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes.
Beat in raisins and pecans.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: "motley"(hamburger sausage)
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours in airtight container.
Take out of refrigerator, mix well again.
Twenty-four hours later roll into 4 lengths.
Bake on broiler pan 5 hours at 200°.

title: corn bread loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, blend egg, milk and shortening; stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 x 4 inch loaf pan. Bake at 425° for 15-18 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 6 x 12-inch pan.
Line with unbroken graham crackers on bottom.
Mix pudding and milk and set; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half over crackers and top with more crackers.
Pour remaining mix over crackers and top with more crackers and frosting.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts.
Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly, or until mixture turns a light caramel color. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Mix to coat well. Spread out to dry.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: hahnchen in estragon(chicken in tarragon)
directions: Chop onion and fry in spoon of butter.
When done, add tarragon vinegar and
let cook down.
When thick, add small amount of wine to resolve.
Put into a heavy pot.
In frypan, brown seasoned, skinless chicken drumsticks in 2 spoons of butter.
Add chicken and tarragon to pot.
Let cook on simmer 25 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: carrot custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots until tender.
Puree carrots with milk and milk powder.
Pour into medium size bowl. Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Pour into six 2/3 cup buttered custard or tea cups.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour boiling water into dish to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.
Garnish with wheat germ, if desired.

title: grated potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and soak in cold water several hours.
Then grate potatoes, drain and add the onions and eggs.
Stir in salt and flour.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into frying pan.
Turn to brown other side.
Serve hot.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix together and add a dash of onion salt, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix next 6 ingredients for sauce; mix with broccoli.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Toss cracker crumbs with melted butter; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frosting for chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 box powdered sugar, nuts, and vanilla.
Pour over hot cake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; pour 1/2 of batter in pan.
Sprinkle the hamburger, pepper, onion and cheese, then remainder of batter and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from oranges and pineapple with dry pudding.
Stir well.
Add fruit.
Refrigerate.
Slice bananas before serving.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Pour hot water, not boiling water, into 9 x 15-inch pan, ungreased.
Add brown sugar, cocoa and marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix according to package and spoon over water mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream and Cool Whip.

title: chicken and sweet potato bake
directions: Dust chicken with flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Saute lightly in oil; arrange in a large casserole or pan.
Add celery, green pepper, garlic, thyme, bay leaf and rosemary to drippings. Cook 5 minutes; stir in remaining seasoned flour and gradually blend in soup and liquid.
Arrange onions and sweet potatoes around chicken in casserole.
Pour seasoned soup over all.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: quiche zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased glass pan, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch deep or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake uncovered for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Add olives and cover with dressing. Refrigerate.

title: fudge
directions: Use a large pot.
Put sugar, milk and butter in pot and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, once it starts to boil.
Let it boil for 8 minutes.
Add other ingredients and beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
